1
00:00:00,398 --> 00:00:04,028
(Couds decorate the early summer sky.)

2
00:00:05,168 --> 00:00:08,438
(A port where gentle ripples welcome you)

3
00:00:09,768 --> 00:00:13,278
(Today's trip starts at the southern coast.)

4
00:00:14,538 --> 00:00:15,778
- Hello.
- Hello.

5
00:00:16,508 --> 00:00:17,647
(Ki Taek is the first to arrive.)

6
00:00:17,648 --> 00:00:19,147
- Hi.
- Hello.

7
00:00:19,148 --> 00:00:20,248
(Yong Jin's here too.)

8
00:00:20,748 --> 00:00:23,318
It feels good to see the sea.

9
00:00:23,488 --> 00:00:24,488
It's nice.

10
00:00:24,489 --> 00:00:25,747
(It's early, but the sea lifts their spirits.)

11
00:00:25,748 --> 00:00:27,418
- Did you get some sleep?
- Yes.

12
00:00:28,358 --> 00:00:30,288
- When did you get here?
- Well...

13
00:00:30,728 --> 00:00:32,957
- Yesterday?
- Today.

14
00:00:32,958 --> 00:00:34,657
Don't you need a small bag?

15
00:00:34,658 --> 00:00:35,997
- You do.
- Yes.

16
00:00:35,998 --> 00:00:38,227
I'll put my stuff in yours.

17
00:00:38,228 --> 00:00:39,267
Sure.

18
00:00:39,268 --> 00:00:40,338
Did you eat something?

19
00:00:40,498 --> 00:00:42,237
- On the way here.
- You ate?

20
00:00:42,238 --> 00:00:44,138
- I had a sandwich in Seoul.
- Did you?

21
00:00:44,538 --> 00:00:46,008
You never know when you'll eat here.

22
00:00:47,178 --> 00:00:48,438
- Maybe 2pm?
- 2pm?

23
00:00:49,078 --> 00:00:50,777
Why are we holding hands like this?

24
00:00:50,778 --> 00:00:52,818
(The two rookies hold hands with interlaced fingers.)

25
00:00:53,118 --> 00:00:55,077
- Hello.
- Hello.

26
00:00:55,078 --> 00:00:56,448
- Hello.
- Hello.

27
00:00:56,788 --> 00:00:57,817
Hello.

28
00:00:57,818 --> 00:00:59,717
- It's nice to be by the sea.
- Yes.

29
00:00:59,718 --> 00:01:00,888
I like the sea.

30
00:01:02,018 --> 00:01:03,088
The water's...

31
00:01:04,328 --> 00:01:05,687
- It's a lovely day.
- Yes.

32
00:01:05,688 --> 00:01:07,057
(It's their second trip and even the sea fascinates them.)

33
00:01:07,058 --> 00:01:08,757
You both dressed so differently...

34
00:01:08,758 --> 00:01:10,128
from your first appearance last time

35
00:01:11,298 --> 00:01:14,698
(They started off in a full-on suit last time.)

36
00:01:15,368 --> 00:01:16,907
You look much more laid back.

37
00:01:16,908 --> 00:01:17,938
I am.

38
00:01:18,738 --> 00:01:20,377
- Hey!
- You're here.

39
00:01:20,378 --> 00:01:21,838
- Yes, Yong Jin.
- Hi.

40
00:01:22,678 --> 00:01:23,707
Hey.

41
00:01:23,708 --> 00:01:24,807
- Thank you.
- Sure.

42
00:01:24,808 --> 00:01:27,148
- What are you grinning about?
- The superstar's here.

43
00:01:28,048 --> 00:01:30,248
What a view. It's so clean and clear.

44
00:01:30,388 --> 00:01:32,148
What a beautiful day it is.

45
00:01:32,788 --> 00:01:34,157
- It's far away.
- We traveled far.

46
00:01:34,158 --> 00:01:35,158
We did.

47
00:01:35,159 --> 00:01:37,728
It took me six hours and I got here yesterday.

48
00:01:37,958 --> 00:01:39,897
Everyone but you got here today, then.

49
00:01:39,898 --> 00:01:40,898
Yes.

50
00:01:41,028 --> 00:01:42,697
Early this morning, at a restaurant nearby,

51
00:01:42,698 --> 00:01:44,098
- I was having breakfast.
- Yes.

52
00:01:44,628 --> 00:01:47,097
Joon walked in doing this.

53
00:01:47,098 --> 00:01:49,198
(Tired Joon walked in like a zombie.)

54
00:01:49,438 --> 00:01:51,068
"Where are we?"

55
00:01:51,708 --> 00:01:54,578
He couldn't open his eyes.

56
00:01:54,878 --> 00:01:56,248
I think he was up all night.

57
00:01:56,308 --> 00:01:57,377
You didn't sleep, did you?

58
00:01:57,378 --> 00:01:59,048
I haven't slept in over 24 hours.

59
00:01:59,548 --> 00:02:00,777
Why didn't you sleep?

60
00:02:00,778 --> 00:02:01,877
I filmed a drama.

61
00:02:01,878 --> 00:02:02,887
Did you really?

62
00:02:02,888 --> 00:02:05,488
A drama... Why?

63
00:02:05,988 --> 00:02:07,157
Why?

64
00:02:07,158 --> 00:02:08,287
Why else...

65
00:02:08,288 --> 00:02:09,987
That's my actual job.

66
00:02:09,988 --> 00:02:11,728
What should I say if you ask why?

67
00:02:11,888 --> 00:02:13,898
We barely made you a star with the dance challenges.

68
00:02:14,528 --> 00:02:15,958
Why did you switch to a drama?

69
00:02:16,328 --> 00:02:17,468
Have you lost your mind?

70
00:02:17,968 --> 00:02:19,027
You just found your niche.

71
00:02:19,028 --> 00:02:20,798
- It'll change your image.
- What's funny is...

72
00:02:20,868 --> 00:02:23,238
That's why I can't film any dance challenges now.

73
00:02:23,538 --> 00:02:24,867
I was so surprised this morning.

74
00:02:24,868 --> 00:02:26,068
He came in with this face.

75
00:02:26,678 --> 00:02:27,807
- He's...
- "Where are we?"

76
00:02:27,808 --> 00:02:29,007
He asked where we were.

77
00:02:29,008 --> 00:02:30,248
He can barely open his eyes even now.

78
00:02:31,420 --> 00:02:32,690
(Laughing)

79
00:02:32,790 --> 00:02:34,119
Tell them what you worried about this morning.

80
00:02:34,120 --> 00:02:35,460
What you said as soon as you got here.

81
00:02:35,620 --> 00:02:36,889
- You were worried?
- Yes.

82
00:02:36,890 --> 00:02:39,430
My worry was... What will we do today?

83
00:02:39,700 --> 00:02:40,799
We always worry about that.

84
00:02:40,800 --> 00:02:41,859
What will we do today?

85
00:02:41,860 --> 00:02:43,899
And then... What should I say?

86
00:02:43,900 --> 00:02:45,569
I worried about stuff like that.

87
00:02:45,570 --> 00:02:47,269
- How to start?
- Yes.

88
00:02:47,270 --> 00:02:49,569
He worried about what to wear and stuff.

89
00:02:49,570 --> 00:02:51,639
His wardrobe and things like that.

90
00:02:51,640 --> 00:02:54,009
There are levels as you know, Yong Jin.

91
00:02:54,010 --> 00:02:55,139
Level one is worry.

92
00:02:55,140 --> 00:02:57,379
"What do we do tomorrow? What should I do?"

93
00:02:57,380 --> 00:02:58,909
That's level one.

94
00:02:58,910 --> 00:03:00,279
"I'll just have fun."

95
00:03:00,280 --> 00:03:02,219
"I'm done for. This is my weekend now."

96
00:03:02,220 --> 00:03:03,920
People like him are at the highest level.

97
00:03:04,350 --> 00:03:06,120
(What level is the expert on?)

98
00:03:06,520 --> 00:03:07,619
"Where am I?"

99
00:03:07,620 --> 00:03:08,789
(Who am I?)

100
00:03:08,790 --> 00:03:09,860
"Where am I?"

101
00:03:10,490 --> 00:03:11,590
(Laughing)

102
00:03:12,060 --> 00:03:13,199
That's the highest level.

103
00:03:13,200 --> 00:03:14,700
"Where do we go from here?"

104
00:03:15,360 --> 00:03:17,300
"Where do we go from here?"

105
00:03:17,630 --> 00:03:19,370
I think he said this to me earlier.

106
00:03:19,840 --> 00:03:21,040
"What are you doing here?"

107
00:03:21,500 --> 00:03:23,009
"Who are you?"

108
00:03:23,010 --> 00:03:24,170
"Why are you here, Yong Jin?"

109
00:03:24,270 --> 00:03:25,739
- "Where am I?"
- You know who he is, right?

110
00:03:25,740 --> 00:03:26,939
Of course I do.

111
00:03:26,940 --> 00:03:28,209
We filmed together once before.

112
00:03:28,210 --> 00:03:29,709
- Yes.
- This is his second trip.

113
00:03:29,710 --> 00:03:30,779
Our second trip.

114
00:03:30,780 --> 00:03:32,010
How are you finding the second trip?

115
00:03:32,480 --> 00:03:34,419
(A high-class question from the variety expert)

116
00:03:34,420 --> 00:03:35,950
- How is it?
- It's great.

117
00:03:36,450 --> 00:03:37,590
It's great.

118
00:03:37,690 --> 00:03:38,719
- I'm excited.
- Are you?

119
00:03:38,720 --> 00:03:40,960
- He would be excited for now.
- I'm excited.

120
00:03:41,520 --> 00:03:44,460
We filmed the newbies' first trip exactly two weeks ago.

121
00:03:45,590 --> 00:03:48,629
(Their tough initiation...)

122
00:03:48,630 --> 00:03:52,900
(was filmed deep in Jeongseon.)

123
00:03:53,200 --> 00:03:55,339
(They slept outdoors in a tent,)

124
00:03:55,340 --> 00:03:58,610
(and even got into the stream.)

125
00:03:59,040 --> 00:04:00,810
How did you feel afterwards?

126
00:04:01,410 --> 00:04:03,309
- The ice-cold water was killer.
- It felt...

127
00:04:03,310 --> 00:04:05,149
like brain freeze when you eat ice cream too quickly.

128
00:04:05,150 --> 00:04:06,449
- It's numbing.
- Yes.

129
00:04:06,450 --> 00:04:08,119
It didn't look that cold on screen.

130
00:04:08,120 --> 00:04:09,120
- Right.
- Exactly.

131
00:04:09,121 --> 00:04:10,649
I felt like my flesh was ripping.

132
00:04:10,650 --> 00:04:12,690
My eyes were so swollen.

133
00:04:12,960 --> 00:04:15,059
That's how cold I was.

134
00:04:15,060 --> 00:04:16,060
It was freezing cold.

135
00:04:16,061 --> 00:04:18,129
He's the best at expressing the cold.

136
00:04:18,130 --> 00:04:20,330
When it's hot or cold. You keep talking.

137
00:04:20,730 --> 00:04:21,829
- Don't jump right in.
- Don't.

138
00:04:21,830 --> 00:04:23,369
- That's bad.
- It looks refreshing.

139
00:04:23,370 --> 00:04:24,370
Yes. Don't hold back.

140
00:04:24,370 --> 00:04:25,370
- Don't hold back?
- Be expressive.

141
00:04:25,371 --> 00:04:26,900
- If you're in pain, say so.
- Don't hold back.

142
00:04:27,400 --> 00:04:28,440
(Laughing)

143
00:04:28,640 --> 00:04:29,939
- Don't hold back.
- Don't do that.

144
00:04:29,940 --> 00:04:31,609
Everyone suffers the same.

145
00:04:31,610 --> 00:04:33,210
(Don't hold back. I got it.)

146
00:04:33,540 --> 00:04:35,179
I heard that Yong Jin went jogging.

147
00:04:35,180 --> 00:04:36,510
(After that shoot?)

148
00:04:37,950 --> 00:04:39,009
(You went jogging...)

149
00:04:39,010 --> 00:04:40,219
(after all that torment?)

150
00:04:40,220 --> 00:04:42,990
I said in our group chat that I went jogging.

151
00:04:43,420 --> 00:04:46,919
(I even went jogging.)

152
00:04:46,920 --> 00:04:48,119
- That...
- You lied, didn't you?

153
00:04:48,120 --> 00:04:49,420
- I lay in bed.
- Did you?

154
00:04:50,130 --> 00:04:51,660
- To be honest... I lied.
- You lied?

155
00:04:51,860 --> 00:04:54,499
- Why tell that kind of lie?
- I didn't want to break character.

156
00:04:54,500 --> 00:04:55,729
Why lie about that?

157
00:04:55,730 --> 00:04:57,599
- To keep my character alive.
- Your character?

158
00:04:57,600 --> 00:04:58,669
My invincible character.

159
00:04:58,670 --> 00:04:59,699
I like that.

160
00:04:59,700 --> 00:05:02,099
He suggested we meet up afterward...

161
00:05:02,100 --> 00:05:04,269
for a drink in Geumho-dong.

162
00:05:04,270 --> 00:05:05,569
- That was a lie.
- Was it?

163
00:05:05,570 --> 00:05:07,139
- I had porridge for dinner.
- Did you?

164
00:05:07,140 --> 00:05:08,180
Yes.

165
00:05:08,440 --> 00:05:10,150
Around me, he acted like...

166
00:05:10,310 --> 00:05:12,209
he was made of steel.

167
00:05:12,210 --> 00:05:14,019
(Mouse DinDin thought Nutria Yong Jin was invincible.)

168
00:05:14,020 --> 00:05:15,519
- Let's just go.
- Your shoes...

169
00:05:15,520 --> 00:05:16,720
Everyone's so frail.

170
00:05:17,320 --> 00:05:18,720
All that was a lie.

171
00:05:19,720 --> 00:05:21,019
- I hate that character.
- Do you?

172
00:05:21,020 --> 00:05:22,020
(He's being honest.)

173
00:05:22,190 --> 00:05:24,390
- I'll drop that character.
- After just two weeks...

174
00:05:24,630 --> 00:05:25,759
If this isn't ideal,

175
00:05:25,760 --> 00:05:26,829
tell me right away.

176
00:05:26,830 --> 00:05:28,059
I won't pretend to be strong.

177
00:05:28,060 --> 00:05:29,329
- That character...
- You'll drop it?

178
00:05:29,330 --> 00:05:30,570
I'll drop it.

179
00:05:31,600 --> 00:05:34,800
Today, before I introduce our destination,

180
00:05:34,900 --> 00:05:37,369
I'll show you the base camp.

181
00:05:37,370 --> 00:05:38,370
What?

182
00:05:38,371 --> 00:05:40,680
Let's go right now.

183
00:05:40,880 --> 00:05:42,039
- Where to?
- To the base camp?

184
00:05:42,040 --> 00:05:43,080
- Yes.
- Gosh.

185
00:05:43,850 --> 00:05:45,250
We're going out to sea.

186
00:05:45,380 --> 00:05:46,749
It would be weird not to when we came this far.

187
00:05:46,750 --> 00:05:47,879
- There's a boat right there.
- Yes.

188
00:05:47,880 --> 00:05:48,950
It's way too close.

189
00:05:49,350 --> 00:05:51,650
It's getting harder when it was hard already.

190
00:05:51,890 --> 00:05:53,219
There are many islands nearby.

191
00:05:53,220 --> 00:05:54,220
- Yes.
- Yes.

192
00:05:54,221 --> 00:05:56,829
We might go to an island and fish for sustenance...

193
00:05:56,830 --> 00:05:58,590
- and build a shelter.
- That's the feel I'm getting.

194
00:05:58,760 --> 00:06:01,560
I checked the map and we're at the tip of the mainland.

195
00:06:01,660 --> 00:06:03,729
It would be weird to go on a city tour from here.

196
00:06:03,730 --> 00:06:04,799
"Let's go inland."

197
00:06:04,800 --> 00:06:05,830
- That would be silly.
- Yes.

198
00:06:06,130 --> 00:06:08,970
The weather is amazing. It's a perfect day.

199
00:06:09,200 --> 00:06:10,240
It's really nice.

200
00:06:11,270 --> 00:06:12,310
What a great day.

201
00:06:13,640 --> 00:06:14,739
The clouds are beautiful.

202
00:06:14,740 --> 00:06:15,740
Yes.

203
00:06:15,741 --> 00:06:16,850
The trail of a plane.

204
00:06:18,980 --> 00:06:21,480
- It's beautiful.
- Look at the sky. It's amazing.

205
00:06:21,750 --> 00:06:22,920
What a lovely day.

206
00:06:23,550 --> 00:06:24,820
The sky's so pretty.

207
00:06:26,190 --> 00:06:28,289
(The sky is extra beautiful...)

208
00:06:28,290 --> 00:06:31,260
(from a boat out at sea.)

209
00:06:31,590 --> 00:06:33,229
To think that I get to see this.

210
00:06:33,230 --> 00:06:34,429
- Yes.
- On a shoot.

211
00:06:34,430 --> 00:06:37,300
You get to see things you wouldn't in life.

212
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:40,300
(Ki Taek is busy enjoying the view.)

213
00:06:42,540 --> 00:06:44,470
(In a good mood under the beautiful sky!)

214
00:06:45,010 --> 00:06:47,010
(Still staring at the sky)

215
00:06:49,380 --> 00:06:51,210
I don't think we're going too far out.

216
00:06:51,850 --> 00:06:53,079
Isn't it the island right there?

217
00:06:53,080 --> 00:06:54,379
- I think that's it.
- Yes.

218
00:06:54,380 --> 00:06:56,350
- We're there already?
- I think so.

219
00:06:56,820 --> 00:06:58,050
We're nearly there.

220
00:06:58,220 --> 00:06:59,289
- This is...
- We're here.

221
00:06:59,290 --> 00:07:00,559
It's almost a city.

222
00:07:00,560 --> 00:07:02,060
- It's not bad.
- It's great.

223
00:07:03,030 --> 00:07:04,590
There are vehicles too.

224
00:07:05,230 --> 00:07:06,959
An island with vehicles...

225
00:07:06,960 --> 00:07:09,129
means there are lots of residents.

226
00:07:09,130 --> 00:07:10,200
- Yes.
- Right?

227
00:07:10,800 --> 00:07:12,569
This is nothing to us.

228
00:07:12,570 --> 00:07:13,570
(Feeling relaxed)

229
00:07:14,170 --> 00:07:16,470
- That's a bigger island.
- It's bigger, right?

230
00:07:16,740 --> 00:07:18,340
We're not going there. Where are we going?

231
00:07:18,840 --> 00:07:20,479
We're going a bit further.

232
00:07:20,480 --> 00:07:22,509
- What's going on?
- We're just passing by.

233
00:07:22,510 --> 00:07:23,549
(The boat sails on?)

234
00:07:23,550 --> 00:07:24,750
We're passing by.

235
00:07:25,010 --> 00:07:26,480
We turned left.

236
00:07:26,820 --> 00:07:28,280
- Why are we going on?
- Why are we passing by?

237
00:07:28,780 --> 00:07:29,889
This isn't it?

238
00:07:29,890 --> 00:07:32,119
(This isn't the place?)

239
00:07:32,120 --> 00:07:33,289
Where are we going?

240
00:07:33,290 --> 00:07:34,620
- Where are we going?
- Where are we going?

241
00:07:35,220 --> 00:07:36,289
(Murmuring)

242
00:07:36,290 --> 00:07:37,760
Why are we passing by that great island?

243
00:07:38,130 --> 00:07:39,260
Why did we pass it by?

244
00:07:39,660 --> 00:07:41,059
We're going somewhere else completely.

245
00:07:41,060 --> 00:07:42,199
What's going on?

246
00:07:42,200 --> 00:07:43,300
Where are we going?

247
00:07:43,630 --> 00:07:44,830
We're going further ahead?

248
00:07:44,970 --> 00:07:46,270
We're going a bit too far.

249
00:07:46,640 --> 00:07:48,070
We're going in pretty far.

250
00:07:48,640 --> 00:07:49,869
- This is way too much.
- The captain...

251
00:07:49,870 --> 00:07:51,540
can't be mistaken about our base camp, right?

252
00:07:51,840 --> 00:07:52,969
- No.
- No, right?

253
00:07:52,970 --> 00:07:54,010
Right.

254
00:07:54,710 --> 00:07:56,079
(Suspecting the veteran captain)

255
00:07:56,080 --> 00:07:57,150
We're doomed.

256
00:07:57,550 --> 00:07:59,250
I don't know. But I know one thing for sure.

257
00:07:59,580 --> 00:08:01,880
We'll reach Okinawa in 30 minutes at this rate.

258
00:08:02,580 --> 00:08:03,789
- Okinawa.
- Yes.

259
00:08:03,790 --> 00:08:05,620
Yes. We'll reach Okinawa in 30 minutes at this rate.

260
00:08:05,920 --> 00:08:07,590
We're going farther than I expected.

261
00:08:07,760 --> 00:08:09,890
(At that moment...)

262
00:08:13,230 --> 00:08:14,359
- What's that?
- What is it?

263
00:08:14,360 --> 00:08:16,570
- I see buildings on the island.
- Wait. We're here.

264
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:18,900
- We're going straight.
- It's the base camp.

265
00:08:19,100 --> 00:08:21,139
He's slowing down. We're here.

266
00:08:21,140 --> 00:08:22,700
- I guess that's our base camp.
- Yes.

267
00:08:23,710 --> 00:08:25,240
Hey, that's not a house.

268
00:08:26,010 --> 00:08:28,140
Wait. The roof is gone.

269
00:08:28,480 --> 00:08:31,079
There's no roof. The building is missing a roof.

270
00:08:31,080 --> 00:08:32,950
It looks like this is where they conduct CBR training.

271
00:08:33,620 --> 00:08:35,620
It looks like survival shows would be filmed here.

272
00:08:35,880 --> 00:08:37,750
Right. This is it. Where are we?

273
00:08:38,590 --> 00:08:40,660
(Today's base camp)

274
00:08:40,720 --> 00:08:43,830
(Wando-gun, South Jeolla Province)

275
00:08:44,260 --> 00:08:46,829
(The island is only accessible...)

276
00:08:46,830 --> 00:08:49,130
(by a long boat ride from the mainland.)

277
00:08:50,030 --> 00:08:52,629
(Daehwa Island)

278
00:08:52,630 --> 00:08:55,000
(Also known as a deserted island)

279
00:08:55,700 --> 00:08:59,780
(Mission: Survive on the deserted island.)

280
00:09:00,510 --> 00:09:03,009
(Those who cannot survive will be...)

281
00:09:03,010 --> 00:09:05,880
(What will happen to the 6 of them?)

282
00:09:06,250 --> 00:09:07,649
I doubt we'll be able to leave this island.

283
00:09:07,650 --> 00:09:08,749
It looks like an abandoned building.

284
00:09:08,750 --> 00:09:10,490
(Getting an ominous feeling)

285
00:09:11,990 --> 00:09:14,460
- I have a bad feeling about this.
- Hey.

286
00:09:14,660 --> 00:09:15,989
There's no electricity here.

287
00:09:15,990 --> 00:09:17,159
(Spotting it right away)

288
00:09:17,160 --> 00:09:18,959
If there's no electricity, how will we get water to wash up?

289
00:09:18,960 --> 00:09:20,300
We probably won't be able to get any.

290
00:09:20,430 --> 00:09:21,729
We'll have to use the seawater.

291
00:09:21,730 --> 00:09:22,860
- Really?
- Yes.

292
00:09:23,400 --> 00:09:24,429
Well...

293
00:09:24,430 --> 00:09:25,630
(They get off the boat for now.)

294
00:09:25,870 --> 00:09:27,039
Director Joo, how did you find...

295
00:09:27,040 --> 00:09:28,169
- a place like this?
- Pardon?

296
00:09:28,170 --> 00:09:29,909
How did you find... I mean...

297
00:09:29,910 --> 00:09:31,570
(The 1st shoot in the wilderness, the 2nd shoot on a deserted island)

298
00:09:31,970 --> 00:09:35,210
This island looks more deserted than the one in "Cast Away."

299
00:09:35,380 --> 00:09:37,880
- All right.
- You are now...

300
00:09:38,250 --> 00:09:39,849
on Daehwa Island...

301
00:09:39,850 --> 00:09:41,780
which boasts beautiful natural scenery...

302
00:09:42,050 --> 00:09:43,319
and a rich marine ecosystem.

303
00:09:43,320 --> 00:09:44,989
- Daehwa Island.
- We're on Daehwa Island?

304
00:09:44,990 --> 00:09:47,620
There used to be residents on this island.

305
00:09:47,960 --> 00:09:50,829
The island used to be lively and had a branch school.

306
00:09:50,830 --> 00:09:52,160
- This island?
- Yes.

307
00:09:52,290 --> 00:09:53,700
It used to be.

308
00:09:55,300 --> 00:09:56,330
But now,

309
00:09:57,500 --> 00:09:59,130
no one lives on this island. It's a deserted island.

310
00:10:00,570 --> 00:10:01,800
I guess everyone moved out.

311
00:10:02,640 --> 00:10:04,269
So we must figure out a way to feed ourselves,

312
00:10:04,270 --> 00:10:05,439
take care of basic needs, and sleep on this island.

313
00:10:05,440 --> 00:10:07,039
- Yes.
- How do we do that?

314
00:10:07,040 --> 00:10:08,180
- Do we have to catch something?
- Okay.

315
00:10:08,840 --> 00:10:10,480
- As for this island, - Okay.

316
00:10:10,750 --> 00:10:12,210
- only one of you...
- What?

317
00:10:12,350 --> 00:10:14,380
- can check in.
- What?

318
00:10:16,050 --> 00:10:18,490
The five members who won't have to stay on this island...

319
00:10:18,890 --> 00:10:21,559
Do you remember the pretty island you pointed out earlier?

320
00:10:21,560 --> 00:10:22,560
- Yes.
- Geumdang Island.

321
00:10:22,561 --> 00:10:25,990
Those of you who won't stay here can spend time on Geumdang Island,

322
00:10:26,190 --> 00:10:28,330
the populated neighboring island.

323
00:10:29,100 --> 00:10:30,329
(They were excited for a second.)

324
00:10:30,330 --> 00:10:31,530
(I see a lot of cars on the island.)

325
00:10:31,870 --> 00:10:32,870
(Crowded with cars)

326
00:10:32,871 --> 00:10:34,899
(The island seemed very appealing.)

327
00:10:34,900 --> 00:10:36,910
(It's not a deserted island for sure.)

328
00:10:37,410 --> 00:10:39,840
- Only one of us will stay here?
- That's a good thing.

329
00:10:40,040 --> 00:10:42,039
- You want one of us to sleep here?
- If I end up staying here,

330
00:10:42,040 --> 00:10:43,249
I'll feel super frustrated.

331
00:10:43,250 --> 00:10:44,510
- Last time, it was you. Right?
- Right.

332
00:10:44,650 --> 00:10:46,880
I'm usually the unlucky one.

333
00:10:47,520 --> 00:10:49,450
(He has a bad feeling about this.)

334
00:10:49,750 --> 00:10:51,289
I don't think anyone can sleep here.

335
00:10:51,290 --> 00:10:52,489
(Only 1 of them will remain on this island.)

336
00:10:52,490 --> 00:10:53,590
All right, everyone.

337
00:10:53,890 --> 00:10:56,690
We'll proceed with the first check-in...

338
00:10:57,390 --> 00:10:58,559
into the island.

339
00:10:58,560 --> 00:10:59,630
- Great.
- Okay.

340
00:10:59,900 --> 00:11:01,900
Here's the first check-in mission.

341
00:11:02,230 --> 00:11:04,230
It's called Check-in, One, Two, Three.

342
00:11:04,600 --> 00:11:05,730
I'll explain the mission.

343
00:11:06,100 --> 00:11:07,499
For the initial formation,

344
00:11:07,500 --> 00:11:09,669
you will alternate positions down the line.

345
00:11:09,670 --> 00:11:10,809
Sit, stand up, sit, stand up,

346
00:11:10,810 --> 00:11:11,940
- and so on.
- Okay.

347
00:11:12,140 --> 00:11:14,940
I'll say, "Check-in, one, two, three."

348
00:11:15,180 --> 00:11:16,779
If you're the only one standing up...

349
00:11:16,780 --> 00:11:18,810
- or sitting down, - Or sitting down.

350
00:11:19,150 --> 00:11:20,250
you will be...

351
00:11:20,650 --> 00:11:22,879
- the first one to check in.
- Okay.

352
00:11:22,880 --> 00:11:24,520
- Just one.
- Anyone with a different position.

353
00:11:25,220 --> 00:11:26,520
It's the one with a different position.

354
00:11:27,260 --> 00:11:29,359
You can't try to read other people's moves.

355
00:11:29,360 --> 00:11:30,829
- Right. There can't be any delay.
- You have to do it right away.

356
00:11:30,830 --> 00:11:32,889
- Let's do it with our eyes closed.
- Let's close our eyes.

357
00:11:32,890 --> 00:11:34,629
I'll toss away anyone who cheats. Seriously.

358
00:11:34,630 --> 00:11:35,630
- Let's close our eyes.
- Yes, you can do that.

359
00:11:35,631 --> 00:11:37,700
- I'll strike him with a rock.
- Come on.

360
00:11:38,070 --> 00:11:40,070
All right. Are you ready?

361
00:11:41,540 --> 00:11:44,040
We're going to start in this setup.

362
00:11:44,740 --> 00:11:46,340
- Let's do this.
- Here it goes.

363
00:11:46,610 --> 00:11:47,610
Okay.

364
00:11:49,780 --> 00:11:50,850
Okay. Here it goes.

365
00:11:52,680 --> 00:11:54,420
Check in. One, two, three.

366
00:11:55,780 --> 00:11:57,589
- Gosh, it could've been bad for us.
- My gosh.

367
00:11:57,590 --> 00:11:58,590
(They're spared.)

368
00:11:58,591 --> 00:11:59,620
Gosh, this could've been a disaster.

369
00:12:00,860 --> 00:12:01,989
- We could've ended it here.
- Gosh.

370
00:12:01,990 --> 00:12:03,590
- It could've ended in one round.
- It could've been a disaster.

371
00:12:04,190 --> 00:12:05,730
- Here it goes.
- This is driving me crazy.

372
00:12:06,460 --> 00:12:07,959
Check in. One, two, three.

373
00:12:07,960 --> 00:12:09,970
(Check in. One, two, three!)

374
00:12:10,170 --> 00:12:11,170
This is driving me crazy.

375
00:12:11,171 --> 00:12:13,070
- My heart is racing.
- My gosh.

376
00:12:13,230 --> 00:12:14,470
- Hey. Hold on.
- My gosh.

377
00:12:15,000 --> 00:12:16,170
It came so close.

378
00:12:16,910 --> 00:12:18,040
What am I going to do?

379
00:12:18,910 --> 00:12:20,910
- This is crazy.
- Yong Jin manages to survive again.

380
00:12:21,280 --> 00:12:22,509
Here it goes. Check in.

381
00:12:22,510 --> 00:12:23,580
One, two, three.

382
00:12:24,350 --> 00:12:25,579
- What a relief.
- Again.

383
00:12:25,580 --> 00:12:27,150
Check in. One, two, three.

384
00:12:29,020 --> 00:12:30,249
You have to make it clear, Se Yoon.

385
00:12:30,250 --> 00:12:31,349
- What is that?
- Crouch down properly.

386
00:12:31,350 --> 00:12:32,449
- He did crouch down.
- Fatties...

387
00:12:32,450 --> 00:12:33,820
can easily fall backward.

388
00:12:34,520 --> 00:12:36,620
- Have you ever been fat?
- I didn't know.

389
00:12:36,760 --> 00:12:38,529
- Apologize now.
- I'm sorry.

390
00:12:38,530 --> 00:12:39,589
All right.

391
00:12:39,590 --> 00:12:41,329
(He averts the crisis by yelling at DinDin.)

392
00:12:41,330 --> 00:12:42,930
Check in. One, two, three.

393
00:12:43,700 --> 00:12:45,129
(They're spared again.)

394
00:12:45,130 --> 00:12:47,200
- Let's keep going.
- This is crazy.

395
00:12:47,540 --> 00:12:49,040
Check in. One, two, three.

396
00:12:52,040 --> 00:12:53,240
- You...
- Hey.

397
00:12:53,440 --> 00:12:54,880
- Thank you.
- My gosh.

398
00:12:55,710 --> 00:12:57,179
Why do you keep messing it up?

399
00:12:57,180 --> 00:12:58,379
(The Russian roulette keeps going.)

400
00:12:58,380 --> 00:12:59,380
I'm feeling dizzy.

401
00:12:59,381 --> 00:13:00,650
- I'm dizzy too.
- Okay.

402
00:13:00,850 --> 00:13:03,020
Here it goes. Check in. One, two, three.

403
00:13:04,990 --> 00:13:06,289
(The rodents assemble once again.)

404
00:13:06,290 --> 00:13:07,460
It's not ending.

405
00:13:08,660 --> 00:13:09,889
- Let's keep matching positions.
- Okay. Let's do this.

406
00:13:09,890 --> 00:13:11,490
- Okay.
- Let's begin.

407
00:13:11,590 --> 00:13:12,859
No chatting. You can't do that.

408
00:13:12,860 --> 00:13:14,099
- He can't do this.
- It was him.

409
00:13:14,100 --> 00:13:15,559
- He wanted to match positions.
- Come on.

410
00:13:15,560 --> 00:13:17,600
- My gosh.
- What's wrong with you?

411
00:13:18,330 --> 00:13:20,340
- This isn't right. Se Yoon.
- Come on.

412
00:13:20,500 --> 00:13:22,139
- I was testing him.
- All right.

413
00:13:22,140 --> 00:13:23,140
- Let's do this.
- Don't do that.

414
00:13:23,140 --> 00:13:24,140
- Okay.
- Okay.

415
00:13:25,210 --> 00:13:26,440
This is driving me crazy.

416
00:13:27,510 --> 00:13:29,180
Check in. One, two, three.

417
00:13:30,410 --> 00:13:31,410
(They're spared.)

418
00:13:31,880 --> 00:13:33,480
Check in. One, two, three.

419
00:13:34,950 --> 00:13:36,420
- Just stand up.
- All right.

420
00:13:36,480 --> 00:13:38,050
Check in. One, two, three.

421
00:13:40,020 --> 00:13:41,460
One, two, three.

422
00:13:43,490 --> 00:13:45,760
- I told you to get up.
- What is this?

423
00:13:45,830 --> 00:13:47,659
Stand up, everyone.

424
00:13:47,660 --> 00:13:49,300
(Lee Yong Jin will remain on the deserted island.)

425
00:13:49,560 --> 00:13:50,570
(Cheering)

426
00:13:50,830 --> 00:13:53,099
- What?
- I told you to get up.

427
00:13:53,100 --> 00:13:55,040
(Celebrating wholeheartedly)

428
00:13:55,200 --> 00:13:56,269
That was good.

429
00:13:56,270 --> 00:13:57,339
Hey, you were great.

430
00:13:57,340 --> 00:13:58,539
- I told you.
- Of course.

431
00:13:58,540 --> 00:13:59,770
Yes. I can read the room.

432
00:14:00,040 --> 00:14:02,340
He's going to need his suit. Right?

433
00:14:03,680 --> 00:14:04,780
My gosh. This is...

434
00:14:05,910 --> 00:14:08,179
Yong Jin, congratulations on becoming the first member...

435
00:14:08,180 --> 00:14:10,749
- to check into the island.
- Yes.

436
00:14:10,750 --> 00:14:11,820
All right.

437
00:14:12,090 --> 00:14:14,789
Yong Jin, you can go to the base camp now...

438
00:14:14,790 --> 00:14:16,159
and check in.

439
00:14:16,160 --> 00:14:18,160
- As for the rest of you, - Will we leave?

440
00:14:18,530 --> 00:14:20,329
you will get on the boat.

441
00:14:20,330 --> 00:14:21,729
- Okay. Come on.
- My gosh.

442
00:14:21,730 --> 00:14:22,960
- I get seasick.
- Say goodbye.

443
00:14:23,300 --> 00:14:25,199
- There will be restaurants...
- Yes.

444
00:14:25,200 --> 00:14:26,840
- and bidets in the restrooms.
- Exactly.

445
00:14:27,840 --> 00:14:29,970
- This will be so tough. Poor him.
- Right. Poor him.

446
00:14:30,310 --> 00:14:31,439
Let's go and get ice cream.

447
00:14:31,440 --> 00:14:32,610
Ki Taek, you look very happy.

448
00:14:33,040 --> 00:14:36,140
(It's fine as long as it's not me.)

449
00:14:36,480 --> 00:14:38,349
- There it comes.
- I have a bad feeling about it.

450
00:14:38,350 --> 00:14:39,779
- Okay.
- This can't be a good thing.

451
00:14:39,780 --> 00:14:40,780
It's not.

452
00:14:40,781 --> 00:14:42,479
Make sure to look for food here...

453
00:14:42,480 --> 00:14:43,749
- in case we have to come back.
- What?

454
00:14:43,750 --> 00:14:44,789
Right. Catch something for food.

455
00:14:44,790 --> 00:14:45,919
- Dried some seaweed or something.
- Yong Jin.

456
00:14:45,920 --> 00:14:47,690
- This can't be good for sure.
- Right.

457
00:14:48,120 --> 00:14:49,489
- Let's get going now.
- Okay.

458
00:14:49,490 --> 00:14:50,560
- Okay. Bye.
- What a pity.

459
00:14:50,830 --> 00:14:52,330
- My gosh.
- What a pity.

460
00:14:52,660 --> 00:14:53,660
Bye.

461
00:14:53,661 --> 00:14:54,899
Switch places with me.

462
00:14:54,900 --> 00:14:56,900
- Bye.
- My gosh.

463
00:14:57,100 --> 00:14:58,670
Good luck, Yong Jin. Hang in there.

464
00:14:59,300 --> 00:15:00,470
Hang in there.

465
00:15:01,400 --> 00:15:03,239
Take care of yourself until the holidays.

466
00:15:03,240 --> 00:15:04,910
- Okay. Come again.
- Okay.

467
00:15:05,440 --> 00:15:06,809
- My gosh.
- Good luck, Yong Jin.

468
00:15:06,810 --> 00:15:08,580
He reminds me of myself from two years ago.

469
00:15:08,880 --> 00:15:09,880
Yong Jin.

470
00:15:09,881 --> 00:15:11,610
Do the munching thing for us.

471
00:15:12,310 --> 00:15:14,049
(Munching)

472
00:15:14,050 --> 00:15:15,250
I can't move my lips.

473
00:15:15,820 --> 00:15:17,019
I'm infuriated.

474
00:15:17,020 --> 00:15:18,250
(He's too frustrated to do his special act.)

475
00:15:18,820 --> 00:15:20,419
- He's abandoned.
- This is so annoying.

476
00:15:20,420 --> 00:15:22,320
- Yong Jin, rest up!
- He's abandoned.

477
00:15:23,260 --> 00:15:24,530
- Bye.
- Okay.

478
00:15:24,630 --> 00:15:26,060
Yong Jin, if you have any cravings,

479
00:15:26,930 --> 00:15:28,029
just think about the food.

480
00:15:28,030 --> 00:15:30,230
Bring Home Run Ball back for me!

481
00:15:31,000 --> 00:15:33,870
(Getting farther away from the abandoned member, Yong Jin)

482
00:15:34,200 --> 00:15:35,999
- We're lucky, right?
- Yes, we're lucky.

483
00:15:36,000 --> 00:15:37,569
If you're alone on the island,

484
00:15:37,570 --> 00:15:40,809
you would have to build a house all on your own.

485
00:15:40,810 --> 00:15:42,110
You would have to do all sorts of things.

486
00:15:42,210 --> 00:15:43,379
There's nothing on the island.

487
00:15:43,380 --> 00:15:45,010
We'd have to build the roof and everything else.

488
00:15:45,580 --> 00:15:48,149
Yong Jin is a positive guy.

489
00:15:48,150 --> 00:15:49,320
- So he might like it.
- Right.

490
00:15:49,450 --> 00:15:50,790
- He's a positive guy.
- He can do it.

491
00:15:51,150 --> 00:15:53,220
How are we going to wash up there?

492
00:15:53,420 --> 00:15:54,489
We can't.

493
00:15:54,490 --> 00:15:56,360
(The boat leaves the island without any delay.)

494
00:15:56,720 --> 00:15:59,290
(Yong Jin is left all alone on the island.)

495
00:16:00,260 --> 00:16:02,060
It's just us on the island?

496
00:16:03,500 --> 00:16:04,629
(The size of the staff has gotten small.)

497
00:16:04,630 --> 00:16:05,829
- It's just us here.
- Really?

498
00:16:05,830 --> 00:16:06,830
Yes.

499
00:16:07,200 --> 00:16:09,170
(Feeling bitter)

500
00:16:10,140 --> 00:16:12,710
I saw a lot of cool places earlier.

501
00:16:13,580 --> 00:16:16,039
I saw a trail next to the rocks. There were many cool spots.

502
00:16:16,040 --> 00:16:17,049
(Leaving behind the beautiful sights of Geumdang Island,)

503
00:16:17,050 --> 00:16:18,050
(he remains on the deserted island alone.)

504
00:16:18,580 --> 00:16:23,720
(What am I going to do now?)

505
00:16:24,350 --> 00:16:25,350
Let's get going.

506
00:16:25,351 --> 00:16:27,860
(Let's get going.)

507
00:16:30,690 --> 00:16:32,090
- Yong Jin.
- Yes.

508
00:16:32,490 --> 00:16:35,029
You're the first to check into the island. Welcome.

509
00:16:35,030 --> 00:16:36,060
Okay.

510
00:16:36,330 --> 00:16:37,999
To help you survive the night on the deserted island,

511
00:16:38,000 --> 00:16:39,099
- Please.
- we'll give you...

512
00:16:39,100 --> 00:16:40,599
a welcome kit we put together.

513
00:16:40,600 --> 00:16:41,670
- Please. Okay.
- Okay.

514
00:16:42,000 --> 00:16:43,569
We'll give that to you first.

515
00:16:43,570 --> 00:16:45,209
(A welcome kit?)

516
00:16:45,210 --> 00:16:46,239
Take this.

517
00:16:46,240 --> 00:16:47,579
(Handing over the special welcome kit for him)

518
00:16:47,580 --> 00:16:49,280
- Here you go.
- Okay.

519
00:16:50,350 --> 00:16:53,250
(What's inside the welcome kit?)

520
00:16:53,750 --> 00:16:57,489
(Ropes)

521
00:16:57,490 --> 00:16:58,690
A shovel and ropes.

522
00:16:59,250 --> 00:17:00,260
Yes.

523
00:17:02,020 --> 00:17:03,490
- This is it?
- Yes.

524
00:17:04,660 --> 00:17:07,030
(There isn't a single person on the deserted island.)

525
00:17:07,300 --> 00:17:10,729
(Current possessions: 2 bottles of water, ropes, and a shovel)

526
00:17:10,730 --> 00:17:13,870
You can freely set up and decorate the base camp...

527
00:17:14,200 --> 00:17:16,000
where you will spend the night.

528
00:17:21,740 --> 00:17:22,780
It's gotten too far.

529
00:17:24,110 --> 00:17:25,709
I got super unlucky.

530
00:17:25,710 --> 00:17:27,549
(Even giving up on his fleeting hope)

531
00:17:27,550 --> 00:17:28,680
I got unlucky.

532
00:17:29,620 --> 00:17:30,689
So this wasn't a good thing.

533
00:17:30,690 --> 00:17:32,849
(Staying on the island wasn't a good thing.)

534
00:17:32,850 --> 00:17:34,989
It's a good thing. You're the first one to check in.

535
00:17:34,990 --> 00:17:36,090
(Water spurting out)

536
00:17:36,360 --> 00:17:40,730
(This is ridiculous.)

537
00:17:42,160 --> 00:17:44,469
I don't want you to say things like "It's a good thing" and so on.

538
00:17:44,470 --> 00:17:45,499
- "It's a good thing."
- Right.

539
00:17:45,500 --> 00:17:47,670
- I'll be careful.
- "Isn't this great?"

540
00:17:48,140 --> 00:17:49,839
No one should say things like that here.

541
00:17:49,840 --> 00:17:51,669
This island is known for its breathtaking scenery.

542
00:17:51,670 --> 00:17:52,839
- Of course. It's beautiful here.
- So...

543
00:17:52,840 --> 00:17:54,039
(Feeling lost)

544
00:17:54,040 --> 00:17:56,309
- Can I take a look around here?
- Sure. Go ahead.

545
00:17:56,310 --> 00:17:57,980
(How will Yong Jin survive on the deserted island?)

546
00:17:58,086 --> 00:18:02,256
(He sets out to find a spot for the base camp.)

547
00:18:02,710 --> 00:18:04,379
I'm starting to get mad at myself.

548
00:18:04,380 --> 00:18:06,410
(I'm starting to get mad at myself.)

549
00:18:06,611 --> 00:18:08,611
I'm getting mad at myself. I'm so furious.

550
00:18:08,811 --> 00:18:09,941
Well,

551
00:18:11,041 --> 00:18:15,451
I can survive a day with 2L of water.

552
00:18:15,981 --> 00:18:17,780
So I can just focus on surviving.

553
00:18:17,781 --> 00:18:19,020
(Essential drinking water is provided.)

554
00:18:19,021 --> 00:18:20,920
I'm not sure if I can find a place to sleep.

555
00:18:20,921 --> 00:18:22,120
(Yong Jin's current location)

556
00:18:22,121 --> 00:18:23,421
That worries me.

557
00:18:24,521 --> 00:18:25,591
What's this?

558
00:18:26,531 --> 00:18:27,531
Wait.

559
00:18:29,091 --> 00:18:30,261
What's a blue crab doing here?

560
00:18:30,801 --> 00:18:31,801
My gosh.

561
00:18:32,501 --> 00:18:34,430
Come here. Oh, my.

562
00:18:34,431 --> 00:18:35,431
(A wild crab emerges.)

563
00:18:35,432 --> 00:18:36,440
Come here.

564
00:18:36,441 --> 00:18:37,500
Holy crab.

565
00:18:37,501 --> 00:18:39,270
(Nice, holy crab.)

566
00:18:39,271 --> 00:18:40,411
Gosh, forget it. Just go.

567
00:18:41,011 --> 00:18:42,571
No. Fine. I'm going to...

568
00:18:42,941 --> 00:18:44,181
We'll see later.

569
00:18:44,981 --> 00:18:46,350
Let's see if I want the crab later.

570
00:18:46,351 --> 00:18:48,350
(The deserted man on the island isn't desperate yet.)

571
00:18:48,351 --> 00:18:50,580
I can see the signs that people actually lived here.

572
00:18:50,581 --> 00:18:51,621
- Right.
- Yes.

573
00:18:54,891 --> 00:18:56,190
Look at the marks of time.

574
00:18:56,191 --> 00:18:57,991
(The abandoned house is covered in bushes.)

575
00:18:59,091 --> 00:19:00,360
Can I enter the house?

576
00:19:00,361 --> 00:19:02,091
(He bravely enters.)

577
00:19:04,815 --> 00:19:07,254
(But all he sees is a pile of garbage.)

578
00:19:07,255 --> 00:19:08,685
I don't see anything useful here.

579
00:19:10,555 --> 00:19:13,125
(He quickly gets out of the house as he's scared.)

580
00:19:13,295 --> 00:19:15,555
This is giving me the chills. It's only 9am.

581
00:19:16,255 --> 00:19:17,464
It hasn't even been 10am yet.

582
00:19:17,465 --> 00:19:19,265
(It hasn't even been 10am yet.)

583
00:19:19,765 --> 00:19:21,894
I've been looking, but there's no path.

584
00:19:21,895 --> 00:19:23,364
(The deserted island only bears...)

585
00:19:23,365 --> 00:19:24,935
(traces of people, but not a living soul in sight.)

586
00:19:25,005 --> 00:19:27,805
Wait. I guess this used to be a school.

587
00:19:28,675 --> 00:19:29,675
I see a pull-up bar.

588
00:19:29,676 --> 00:19:31,344
(The school yard with signs of students running around here)

589
00:19:31,345 --> 00:19:32,674
There used to be a swing here.

590
00:19:32,675 --> 00:19:34,575
(The school yard with signs of students running around here)

591
00:19:35,445 --> 00:19:36,445
It's the ocean.

592
00:19:36,446 --> 00:19:39,284
(There's an open view of the ocean.)

593
00:19:39,285 --> 00:19:40,885
I think this will be a nice spot...

594
00:19:41,885 --> 00:19:43,185
for the base camp.

595
00:19:43,785 --> 00:19:45,324
It's nice and cool here.

596
00:19:45,325 --> 00:19:46,624
(Flatland perfect for the base camp)

597
00:19:46,625 --> 00:19:47,755
Will it be scary at night?

598
00:19:48,225 --> 00:19:49,494
There's an abandoned school.

599
00:19:49,495 --> 00:19:51,125
(There's a school here.)

600
00:19:51,465 --> 00:19:57,465
(He looks around the school just in case he finds anything.)

601
00:19:58,065 --> 00:19:59,305
I don't see anything, though.

602
00:20:00,305 --> 00:20:03,845
I can't find any tools...

603
00:20:04,205 --> 00:20:06,644
that will help me survive.

604
00:20:06,645 --> 00:20:08,515
(The deserted island is empty for sure.)

605
00:20:08,875 --> 00:20:12,715
(He explores the opposite side of the island.)

606
00:20:13,355 --> 00:20:15,785
The school is a nice spot for the base camp.

607
00:20:16,455 --> 00:20:18,955
It's in the shade. So it's cool and breezy.

608
00:20:19,485 --> 00:20:20,595
All right. I guess...

609
00:20:20,995 --> 00:20:24,095
I shouldn't expect to wash my face or anything today.

610
00:20:24,225 --> 00:20:25,295
- Cement?
- What?

611
00:20:25,665 --> 00:20:26,694
Cement?

612
00:20:26,695 --> 00:20:29,264
(Cement?)

613
00:20:29,265 --> 00:20:31,205
Come on. What are you saying?

614
00:20:31,535 --> 00:20:34,035
I said, "wash." As in washing my face.

615
00:20:34,505 --> 00:20:35,574
Come on.

616
00:20:35,575 --> 00:20:36,634
(Why are you making it harder on me?)

617
00:20:36,635 --> 00:20:38,904
- I...
- What are you saying?

618
00:20:38,905 --> 00:20:40,115
I don't feel good either.

619
00:20:40,345 --> 00:20:41,975
What are you talking about?

620
00:20:42,175 --> 00:20:43,314
Why cement?

621
00:20:43,315 --> 00:20:44,845
- Washing my face.
- Washing.

622
00:20:45,185 --> 00:20:47,114
- You can use whatever you have.
- So...

623
00:20:47,115 --> 00:20:49,514
I don't have anything. I've got nothing.

624
00:20:49,515 --> 00:20:51,355
- You...
- You didn't give me my bag.

625
00:20:51,855 --> 00:20:53,285
- There's nothing in your pockets?
- No.

626
00:20:54,255 --> 00:20:55,994
I only have my resident card and eye drops.

627
00:20:55,995 --> 00:20:58,194
(He only has his ID card and eye drops.)

628
00:20:58,195 --> 00:20:59,525
I'm glad you have eye drops.

629
00:21:01,935 --> 00:21:04,104
I really don't get how you mixed up those two words.

630
00:21:04,105 --> 00:21:07,634
(For some reason, he's feeling even more lost.)

631
00:21:07,635 --> 00:21:08,805
Be careful here.

632
00:21:10,145 --> 00:21:11,175
This isn't easy.

633
00:21:11,905 --> 00:21:14,745
(As soon as he arrives on the other side of the island,)

634
00:21:14,845 --> 00:21:18,985
(he spots piles of seaweed on the shore.)

635
00:21:19,745 --> 00:21:20,785
Let's see.

636
00:21:20,915 --> 00:21:22,185
Wando-gun is famous for seaweed. Right?

637
00:21:22,785 --> 00:21:26,825
(Putting it in his mouth right away)

638
00:21:27,155 --> 00:21:31,865
(How does the wild seaweed, the regional specialty, taste?)

639
00:21:32,395 --> 00:21:35,235
If I were to eat this merely for survival,

640
00:21:35,765 --> 00:21:37,565
I could extend my survival by three hours.

641
00:21:38,965 --> 00:21:42,074
(It means he can't eat it.)

642
00:21:42,075 --> 00:21:43,105
There's nothing here.

643
00:21:43,305 --> 00:21:44,875
How can there be nothing here?

644
00:21:46,075 --> 00:21:47,575
This is southwest.

645
00:21:48,545 --> 00:21:49,644
That's southwest.

646
00:21:49,645 --> 00:21:50,944
(He utilizes all kinds of methods...)

647
00:21:50,945 --> 00:21:52,544
(to explore every nook and corner of the island.)

648
00:21:52,545 --> 00:21:53,785
Right. That's edible.

649
00:21:54,015 --> 00:21:55,285
Gosh, seriously.

650
00:21:56,315 --> 00:21:57,954
These are Japanese rubber gloves.

651
00:21:57,955 --> 00:21:59,425
They must've drifted down here.

652
00:21:59,925 --> 00:22:02,094
- Because we're in the south.
- I guess so.

653
00:22:02,095 --> 00:22:04,124
(He only spots useless garbage.)

654
00:22:04,125 --> 00:22:05,495
I can't use that either.

655
00:22:06,525 --> 00:22:07,565
No.

656
00:22:07,595 --> 00:22:12,865
(He can't find anything useful on the island.)

657
00:22:13,065 --> 00:22:14,135
Se Yoon.

658
00:22:15,235 --> 00:22:16,875
Jong Min. DinDin.

659
00:22:17,475 --> 00:22:18,875
There's nothing I can do here.

660
00:22:20,815 --> 00:22:22,914
(He calls out for his members,)

661
00:22:22,915 --> 00:22:25,545
(but he only hears back the sounds of the waves.)

662
00:22:25,915 --> 00:22:28,885
(The reality of isolation slowly sinks in.)

663
00:22:31,385 --> 00:22:33,025
Why are you wearing sunglasses?

664
00:22:34,755 --> 00:22:38,965
(Picking a fight with the director for no reason)

665
00:22:39,765 --> 00:22:41,934
- I got a question about the format.
- Okay.

666
00:22:41,935 --> 00:22:42,995
- Listen.
- Okay.

667
00:22:43,095 --> 00:22:46,805
"What if one of them gets deserted on the island?"

668
00:22:47,235 --> 00:22:48,834
"I'm sure he'll try this and that."

669
00:22:48,835 --> 00:22:49,974
"What do you think he'll do?"

670
00:22:49,975 --> 00:22:51,074
I'm sure you guys had a meeting about that.

671
00:22:51,075 --> 00:22:52,075
We did.

672
00:22:52,545 --> 00:22:54,475
I take it that the meeting didn't go too well.

673
00:22:54,845 --> 00:22:56,014
We didn't know who would get left behind.

674
00:22:56,015 --> 00:22:57,015
- Right.
- Yes.

675
00:22:58,715 --> 00:23:01,515
So there's nothing you guys set up for me here.

676
00:23:02,055 --> 00:23:04,154
- We're a reality variety show...
- Right.

677
00:23:04,155 --> 00:23:05,155
as you know.

678
00:23:05,156 --> 00:23:09,155
(What do I do?)

679
00:23:09,725 --> 00:23:11,924
Can I say something?

680
00:23:11,925 --> 00:23:12,965
Sure.

681
00:23:13,465 --> 00:23:14,695
The welcome kit...

682
00:23:15,765 --> 00:23:16,834
is lacking.

683
00:23:16,835 --> 00:23:19,135
(The welcome kit is very lacking.)

684
00:23:19,835 --> 00:23:21,874
It seems you agree with me.

685
00:23:21,875 --> 00:23:23,374
(Criticizing the result of the staff's meeting)

686
00:23:23,375 --> 00:23:24,475
Please give me more.

687
00:23:25,305 --> 00:23:26,405
Give me what I need.

688
00:23:26,705 --> 00:23:27,845
What do you need?

689
00:23:28,875 --> 00:23:30,415
I need a roll of toilet paper.

690
00:23:30,885 --> 00:23:32,085
- Toilet paper?
- Yes, toilet paper.

691
00:23:32,285 --> 00:23:34,415
I really need to go number two. I'm serious.

692
00:23:35,855 --> 00:23:37,585
I turned 42 years old this year.

693
00:23:37,855 --> 00:23:39,285
I can't use the branches to wipe myself.

694
00:23:39,855 --> 00:23:40,894
Here you go.

695
00:23:40,895 --> 00:23:43,665
(Handing over the tissues)

696
00:23:43,965 --> 00:23:45,864
(What a surprise.)

697
00:23:45,865 --> 00:23:47,495
(He skeptically takes the tissue packet.)

698
00:23:48,065 --> 00:23:50,935
(A promotional tissue packet from a business)

699
00:23:51,505 --> 00:23:53,364
- Did you check what's inside?
- What?

700
00:23:53,365 --> 00:23:54,905
- You didn't check, right?
- I just had that on me.

701
00:23:55,005 --> 00:23:56,775
There's only one wet wipe left.

702
00:23:57,675 --> 00:23:59,875
- There's only one left.
- That's all I have.

703
00:24:00,675 --> 00:24:01,675
Okay.

704
00:24:01,676 --> 00:24:04,914
(He needs to get creative to take care of his business.)

705
00:24:04,915 --> 00:24:06,085
Let's go back up now.

706
00:24:07,485 --> 00:24:10,485
By the way, I really need to go number two.

707
00:24:10,985 --> 00:24:12,325
I have to take care of it myself, right?

708
00:24:12,985 --> 00:24:15,395
(A moment later)

709
00:24:15,695 --> 00:24:16,754
You know what?

710
00:24:16,755 --> 00:24:17,824
(Yong Jin is back from somewhere.)

711
00:24:17,825 --> 00:24:20,795
You know, I just went to pee since it was urgent.

712
00:24:21,965 --> 00:24:24,235
The color of my urine didn't look good. I must get out.

713
00:24:26,505 --> 00:24:28,504
I mean, I'm serious.

714
00:24:28,505 --> 00:24:31,045
(Upholding his dignity by using his urine as an excuse)

715
00:24:31,605 --> 00:24:33,244
(Masking his sadness with the eye drops from his pocket)

716
00:24:33,245 --> 00:24:35,645
(Masking his sadness with the eye drops from his pocket)

717
00:24:36,985 --> 00:24:38,014
They're hot.

718
00:24:38,015 --> 00:24:39,684
(The eye drops are hot.)

719
00:24:39,685 --> 00:24:40,685
They're hot.

720
00:24:41,215 --> 00:24:42,415
The eye drops are hot.

721
00:24:43,255 --> 00:24:44,684
They're hot since I've been in the sun.

722
00:24:44,685 --> 00:24:46,824
(Nothing is going his way on the deserted island.)

723
00:24:46,825 --> 00:24:48,224
Welcome to Island Paradise, everyone.

724
00:24:48,225 --> 00:24:49,294
(Meanwhile, the 5 survivors...)

725
00:24:49,295 --> 00:24:50,325
Let's go.

726
00:24:50,765 --> 00:24:51,765
This is nice.

727
00:24:51,766 --> 00:24:52,995
(Arriving on the populated island)

728
00:24:53,635 --> 00:24:55,995
It feels like I came back from the dead with a single game.

729
00:24:56,965 --> 00:24:58,065
What's that?

730
00:24:58,705 --> 00:25:00,634
- There's a prize.
- Gosh, no. Guys.

731
00:25:00,635 --> 00:25:02,404
- Are you for real?
- This is a welcome drink.

732
00:25:02,405 --> 00:25:03,405
- It's for us?
- Yes.

733
00:25:03,406 --> 00:25:04,744
- Welcome tea.
- Thank you.

734
00:25:04,745 --> 00:25:05,905
- Here you go, Joon.
- Really?

735
00:25:05,975 --> 00:25:06,975
- Yes. Of course.
- We can just drink it?

736
00:25:06,975 --> 00:25:07,975
- My gosh.
- What?

737
00:25:07,976 --> 00:25:09,814
- Try it.
- This has never happened before.

738
00:25:09,815 --> 00:25:10,984
- But...
- Seriously.

739
00:25:10,985 --> 00:25:12,945
- I always got unlucky.
- I mean...

740
00:25:13,315 --> 00:25:14,685
I've never gotten lucky like this on the show.

741
00:25:15,015 --> 00:25:16,085
It looks good.

742
00:25:16,255 --> 00:25:17,384
(Let me enjoy my lucky break.)

743
00:25:17,385 --> 00:25:19,385
- Really? It's a welcome drink?
- So it's really for us.

744
00:25:19,985 --> 00:25:22,255
- This is so good. My gosh.
- A brunch would be lovely now.

745
00:25:22,625 --> 00:25:24,564
- We get so happy over a drink.
- Like bagels.

746
00:25:24,565 --> 00:25:25,924
(His level of happiness goes up for his first special treatment.)

747
00:25:25,925 --> 00:25:27,735
Welcome to the island, everyone.

748
00:25:27,835 --> 00:25:29,465
This is your destination today.

749
00:25:29,695 --> 00:25:31,835
It's located in Wando-gun, South Jeolla Province.

750
00:25:32,205 --> 00:25:33,775
It's called Geumdang Island.

751
00:25:34,635 --> 00:25:35,974
Having been shaped by nature over a long time,

752
00:25:35,975 --> 00:25:37,305
Geumdang Island offers...

753
00:25:37,805 --> 00:25:39,074
a beautiful harmony...

754
00:25:39,075 --> 00:25:40,314
of unique rock structures and columnar joints.

755
00:25:40,315 --> 00:25:41,645
(A place with columnar joints and unique rock structures)

756
00:25:41,775 --> 00:25:44,245
So it's nicknamed the sculpture park on the ocean.

757
00:25:44,385 --> 00:25:46,484
It's known as a stunning island.

758
00:25:46,485 --> 00:25:48,114
(The sculpture park on the ocean)

759
00:25:48,115 --> 00:25:49,414
You will set out to check out...

760
00:25:49,415 --> 00:25:50,785
eight beautiful sights of the island.

761
00:25:51,125 --> 00:25:53,655
To start you off with 1 of the 8 sights,

762
00:25:53,895 --> 00:25:57,325
you will go and enjoy trekking the Gyoam Cheongpung Trail.

763
00:25:57,365 --> 00:25:59,195
- My gosh.
- That sounds exhausting.

764
00:25:59,625 --> 00:26:01,834
- Trekking doesn't sound good.
- No.

765
00:26:01,835 --> 00:26:03,134
- Let's get going.
- Let's go and walk.

766
00:26:03,135 --> 00:26:04,165
Okay.

767
00:26:05,805 --> 00:26:08,075
- Ki Taek, you're on many shows now.
- It's pretty steep.

768
00:26:08,405 --> 00:26:09,505
I watched your show.

769
00:26:09,835 --> 00:26:11,574
- The one with the monk.
- You did?

770
00:26:11,575 --> 00:26:12,674
- Yes.
- Monk Pomnyun?

771
00:26:12,675 --> 00:26:15,515
I wasn't feeling well when I was filming the show.

772
00:26:15,945 --> 00:26:17,615
I had a severe case of the traveler's diarrhea.

773
00:26:18,015 --> 00:26:20,215
- It must've been tough.
- Yes. So...

774
00:26:20,685 --> 00:26:23,014
- You didn't go prepared.
- Hear me out.

775
00:26:23,015 --> 00:26:24,554
If you had a feeling you'd get the traveler's diarrhea,

776
00:26:24,555 --> 00:26:26,955
you should've gone there a week before and dealt with it in advance.

777
00:26:28,325 --> 00:26:30,125
- This is how he gets them canceled.
- You bet.

778
00:26:30,395 --> 00:26:32,165
- Get a grip.
- Okay.

779
00:26:32,395 --> 00:26:34,865
Ki Taek's career is going well now.

780
00:26:35,565 --> 00:26:38,564
But you will be even more successful in three years.

781
00:26:38,565 --> 00:26:39,664
(A sudden prediction)

782
00:26:39,665 --> 00:26:40,674
- Why do you say that?
- Why?

783
00:26:40,675 --> 00:26:42,134
- I can feel it.
- Really?

784
00:26:42,135 --> 00:26:43,234
(He's bound to be successful.)

785
00:26:43,235 --> 00:26:44,345
(Thank you.)

786
00:26:44,475 --> 00:26:47,345
Whether it's variety shows or something else, do everything.

787
00:26:47,615 --> 00:26:48,644
Exactly.

788
00:26:48,645 --> 00:26:49,945
(A young man radiating a strong sense of success)

789
00:26:50,175 --> 00:26:51,745
I feel like Ki Taek's time is coming.

790
00:26:52,245 --> 00:26:54,084
When they see each other again after three years,

791
00:26:54,085 --> 00:26:55,285
it'd be funny if he pretends not to know Jong Min.

792
00:26:56,055 --> 00:26:57,055
"Hey, Ki Taek. Who..."

793
00:26:57,625 --> 00:26:58,625
(Laughing)

794
00:26:59,985 --> 00:27:01,754
- DinDin would be...
- In three years...

795
00:27:01,755 --> 00:27:03,425
exactly the same for the next three years.

796
00:27:03,495 --> 00:27:04,564
(Laughing)

797
00:27:04,565 --> 00:27:05,794
- Like how I am now?
- Yes.

798
00:27:05,795 --> 00:27:07,534
- Thanks, anyway.
- At least he'd stay the same.

799
00:27:07,535 --> 00:27:08,695
- Exactly.
- Thanks, anyway.

800
00:27:08,765 --> 00:27:10,235
Staying the same is the hardest.

801
00:27:10,635 --> 00:27:11,635
Right.

802
00:27:13,535 --> 00:27:14,905
This is a difficult section.

803
00:27:15,075 --> 00:27:16,235
- A difficult section?
- This is very high.

804
00:27:16,735 --> 00:27:18,145
What? This is practically a rock face.

805
00:27:18,505 --> 00:27:19,645
- Goodness.
- What's this?

806
00:27:19,845 --> 00:27:21,914
Gosh, this is quite high up.

807
00:27:21,915 --> 00:27:25,985
(A slope that's steep enough to make you dizzy)

808
00:27:26,415 --> 00:27:27,655
It's very steep here.

809
00:27:29,085 --> 00:27:30,555
Suddenly, I don't want to keep going.

810
00:27:31,655 --> 00:27:35,325
(It doesn't seem easy for youngest Ki Taek either.)

811
00:27:35,595 --> 00:27:36,695
It's too high.

812
00:27:36,825 --> 00:27:38,425
I think we're at the peak.

813
00:27:38,525 --> 00:27:40,025
Gosh, it's very steep here.

814
00:27:40,595 --> 00:27:41,895
Can't we hold onto this?

815
00:27:42,395 --> 00:27:43,465
(Stumbling)

816
00:27:43,595 --> 00:27:44,804
(The representative of 2 Days 1 Night)

817
00:27:44,805 --> 00:27:46,765
(Even Muscle Man Joon stumbles on the mountain trail.)

818
00:27:47,375 --> 00:27:50,575
(He starts to sweat.)

819
00:27:53,275 --> 00:27:55,414
(A rugged path leading through a narrow gap between the rocks)

820
00:27:55,415 --> 00:27:56,714
- We'd better be careful.
- Okay.

821
00:27:56,715 --> 00:27:59,014
(A rugged path leading through a narrow gap between the rocks)

822
00:27:59,015 --> 00:28:00,485
- On both sides...
- Be careful right here.

823
00:28:00,885 --> 00:28:01,915
Okay.

824
00:28:02,255 --> 00:28:03,825
It's harder than I expected.

825
00:28:05,425 --> 00:28:08,554
(The trail keeps getting narrower.)

826
00:28:08,555 --> 00:28:10,794
- Compared to what I thought...
- It's hard.

827
00:28:10,795 --> 00:28:11,865
(Everyone gets a lot quieter.)

828
00:28:11,995 --> 00:28:13,794
There are rocks underneath,

829
00:28:13,795 --> 00:28:15,335
so please watch your head as you walk.

830
00:28:16,665 --> 00:28:17,805
It's so steep.

831
00:28:18,465 --> 00:28:19,734
It's this way.

832
00:28:19,735 --> 00:28:21,805
(A steep staircase unfolds before them.)

833
00:28:22,375 --> 00:28:23,505
The slope is...

834
00:28:23,945 --> 00:28:25,075
My goodness.

835
00:28:26,075 --> 00:28:29,414
(Careful)

836
00:28:29,415 --> 00:28:32,215
(Taking each step cautiously)

837
00:28:33,245 --> 00:28:35,884
(Walking along the path by a coastal cliff)

838
00:28:35,885 --> 00:28:36,915
We can do this.

839
00:28:37,855 --> 00:28:38,925
Gosh, what's this?

840
00:28:43,055 --> 00:28:44,325
What kind of place is this?

841
00:28:44,565 --> 00:28:45,795
It's so beautiful.

842
00:28:47,565 --> 00:28:48,695
It's magnificent.

843
00:28:49,495 --> 00:28:52,834
(At the end of the steep stairway)

844
00:28:52,835 --> 00:28:57,505
(A breathtaking view where the rocky path meets the sea)

845
00:28:57,805 --> 00:29:00,104
(The members' current location)

846
00:29:00,105 --> 00:29:01,214
This is insane.

847
00:29:01,215 --> 00:29:02,314
(The members' current location)

848
00:29:02,315 --> 00:29:05,014
Ki Taek, it's impossible to carve this. You know that, right?

849
00:29:05,015 --> 00:29:06,015
Yes.

850
00:29:06,615 --> 00:29:08,354
- Only nature can do it.
- Oh, my.

851
00:29:08,355 --> 00:29:09,355
- Right.
- This is...

852
00:29:09,356 --> 00:29:10,484
- It's really beautiful.
- Unbelievable.

853
00:29:10,485 --> 00:29:11,825
Nature is the greatest sculptor.

854
00:29:12,585 --> 00:29:14,025
- Is there more?
- Look at this.

855
00:29:14,795 --> 00:29:15,925
I feel strange.

856
00:29:16,095 --> 00:29:17,194
- Gosh.
- This is...

857
00:29:17,195 --> 00:29:19,324
- Look at this.
- Is there really a path?

858
00:29:19,325 --> 00:29:21,364
- Nature is the greatest sculptor.
- Isn't it built by nature?

859
00:29:21,365 --> 00:29:22,594
Who else could create this?

860
00:29:22,595 --> 00:29:24,835
- Was the path naturally built?
- Only nature could do it.

861
00:29:25,405 --> 00:29:27,165
Only nature could do this.

862
00:29:28,035 --> 00:29:29,604
It's really beautiful here.

863
00:29:29,605 --> 00:29:31,705
- It's majestic.
- Look inside here.

864
00:29:32,505 --> 00:29:33,914
It's truly beautiful.

865
00:29:33,915 --> 00:29:35,815
(Every step brings exclamations of awe.)

866
00:29:36,115 --> 00:29:38,285
(In awe)

867
00:29:38,745 --> 00:29:40,315
You get to experience this on 2 Days 1 Night.

868
00:29:41,085 --> 00:29:43,384
You don't get to come to places like this in everyday life.

869
00:29:43,385 --> 00:29:44,425
Right.

870
00:29:44,485 --> 00:29:46,424
(Experiencing firsthand...)

871
00:29:46,425 --> 00:29:48,355
(the beautiful nature of Korea through traveling)

872
00:29:48,555 --> 00:29:49,794
What kind of route is this?

873
00:29:49,795 --> 00:29:51,324
(Gosh, what kind of route is this?)

874
00:29:51,325 --> 00:29:52,865
- It's a difficult route.
- What?

875
00:29:53,025 --> 00:29:54,165
It's a difficult route.

876
00:29:54,335 --> 00:29:55,665
Hold onto the rope tight.

877
00:29:56,265 --> 00:29:57,335
Is there no path?

878
00:29:57,765 --> 00:29:59,035
No, there's no path.

879
00:30:00,105 --> 00:30:01,205
We must be careful.

880
00:30:01,835 --> 00:30:03,334
(Narrow)

881
00:30:03,335 --> 00:30:04,645
- One, two.
- It's scary.

882
00:30:06,675 --> 00:30:07,775
This is fun.

883
00:30:08,815 --> 00:30:09,974
- This path is...
- It feels like...

884
00:30:09,975 --> 00:30:12,345
- I'm creating a path as I go.
- I agree.

885
00:30:12,945 --> 00:30:14,014
It's really beautiful.

886
00:30:14,015 --> 00:30:15,855
(As they move forward with the spirit of a pioneer)

887
00:30:16,885 --> 00:30:17,955
It looks amazing.

888
00:30:19,225 --> 00:30:21,254
Everything looks like a painting.

889
00:30:21,255 --> 00:30:22,454
There are places to sit.

890
00:30:22,455 --> 00:30:24,195
These seats are created by nature.

891
00:30:25,025 --> 00:30:26,865
And the water looks like a sports drink.

892
00:30:27,535 --> 00:30:29,164
(Gyoam Cheongpung)

893
00:30:29,165 --> 00:30:30,934
(A natural scening wonder...)

894
00:30:30,935 --> 00:30:33,665
(shaped over eons by volcanic rock and weathering)

895
00:30:34,075 --> 00:30:36,234
(Between towering rock cliffs)

896
00:30:36,235 --> 00:30:38,305
(Where a refreshing sea breeze lingers)

897
00:30:38,705 --> 00:30:39,845
It looks beautiful over there.

898
00:30:40,715 --> 00:30:42,075
This place is the best.

899
00:30:42,645 --> 00:30:44,615
It's very nice and cozy.

900
00:30:45,615 --> 00:30:46,785
I love this place.

901
00:30:47,315 --> 00:30:48,514
It's a paradise.

902
00:30:48,515 --> 00:30:50,755
(It feels like paradise.)

903
00:30:51,285 --> 00:30:52,685
- I wish I had some gimbap.
- I know.

904
00:30:53,055 --> 00:30:55,024
- Cup noodles sound amazing now.
- Right?

905
00:30:55,025 --> 00:30:56,894
With some hot broth.

906
00:30:56,895 --> 00:30:58,725
(A scenery so captivating that you want to stay here forever)

907
00:30:59,425 --> 00:31:00,634
This is great.

908
00:31:00,635 --> 00:31:01,694
(Feeling moved beyond words)

909
00:31:01,695 --> 00:31:04,564
Wouldn't it be wonderful to be here with your family?

910
00:31:04,565 --> 00:31:06,005
- This place is amazing.
- With your own family.

911
00:31:06,435 --> 00:31:07,975
Your kids are grown up now, so they wouldn't tag along.

912
00:31:08,805 --> 00:31:09,904
They still tag along.

913
00:31:09,905 --> 00:31:11,074
(Upset)

914
00:31:11,075 --> 00:31:13,304
If I bribe them with some pocket money, they'd come.

915
00:31:13,305 --> 00:31:14,645
Only if you give them money?

916
00:31:15,245 --> 00:31:16,374
You have to bribe them.

917
00:31:16,375 --> 00:31:18,485
(There's someone they've forgotten.)

918
00:31:18,785 --> 00:31:21,415
(I wonder what Yong Jin is up to.)

919
00:31:21,585 --> 00:31:23,014
Say hello to him.

920
00:31:23,015 --> 00:31:24,755
(Let's say hello to Yong Jin.)

921
00:31:25,055 --> 00:31:27,555
This will fly directly to Yong Jin.

922
00:31:28,195 --> 00:31:29,795
- Yong Jin.
- Go to Yong Jin.

923
00:31:30,425 --> 00:31:31,465
2 Days...

924
00:31:31,695 --> 00:31:32,964
- 1 Night.
- 1 Night.

925
00:31:32,965 --> 00:31:36,634
(Yong Jin, we're having so much fun.)

926
00:31:36,635 --> 00:31:38,865
Shall we pick up our pace?

927
00:31:39,705 --> 00:31:42,305
(At the same time, on the deserted island)

928
00:31:42,705 --> 00:31:44,905
(Scouting)

929
00:31:45,575 --> 00:31:47,544
I bet there aren't even animals here.

930
00:31:47,545 --> 00:31:49,375
(I bet there aren't even animals here.)

931
00:31:49,615 --> 00:31:51,015
Anyway, my base camp is...

932
00:31:51,945 --> 00:31:53,715
The ground is soft. Can you believe it?

933
00:31:54,515 --> 00:31:58,625
The trees provide shade from the sun.

934
00:31:59,425 --> 00:32:01,895
This will be my base camp.

935
00:32:01,995 --> 00:32:03,055
- Okay.
- Yes.

936
00:32:03,555 --> 00:32:06,024
It's a perfectly suitable place. Nowhere is better than this.

937
00:32:06,025 --> 00:32:07,195
(Base camp at the abandoned school site)

938
00:32:07,495 --> 00:32:11,565
(Let me take a break.)

939
00:32:11,805 --> 00:32:15,035
If I had a fishing rod, I'd try to fish.

940
00:32:15,335 --> 00:32:17,375
But I have no tools or equipment.

941
00:32:18,175 --> 00:32:19,345
A fishing rod...

942
00:32:19,905 --> 00:32:20,915
What?

943
00:32:21,175 --> 00:32:22,344
You don't know how to make it?

944
00:32:22,345 --> 00:32:25,145
(You don't know how to make it?)

945
00:32:25,415 --> 00:32:29,255
(Unbelievable)

946
00:32:31,625 --> 00:32:34,125
You're quite funny.

947
00:32:34,425 --> 00:32:36,425
How can I make a fishing rod?

948
00:32:36,625 --> 00:32:37,895
What about a fishing hook?

949
00:32:38,565 --> 00:32:41,295
(He finds a pile of bamboo someone must've left behind.)

950
00:32:41,835 --> 00:32:42,895
Shall I try it?

951
00:32:44,505 --> 00:32:45,535
Hold on.

952
00:32:46,235 --> 00:32:48,604
(Activating AI)

953
00:32:48,605 --> 00:32:50,335
How to make a fishing rod on a deserted island.

954
00:32:51,145 --> 00:32:54,045
Making a fishing rod yourself could be fun.

955
00:32:54,415 --> 00:32:57,545
If you find a sturdy branch or bamboo nearby...

956
00:32:57,785 --> 00:33:00,585
and tie some rope to it, you can turn it into a straight fishing rod.

957
00:33:00,955 --> 00:33:02,055
What about bait?

958
00:33:03,355 --> 00:33:04,385
Bait.

959
00:33:05,055 --> 00:33:07,795
For bait, you can use things found in nature around you.

960
00:33:08,125 --> 00:33:10,355
Dig up some earth and catch an insect.

961
00:33:10,525 --> 00:33:13,095
You can also use shellfish or small fish as bait.

962
00:33:13,595 --> 00:33:16,964
(The method is more realistic than he thought.)

963
00:33:16,965 --> 00:33:18,264
How can I use small fish...

964
00:33:18,265 --> 00:33:20,235
as bait to catch another fish?

965
00:33:22,235 --> 00:33:23,304
Let's see.

966
00:33:23,305 --> 00:33:25,404
(He's about to make a fishing rod.)

967
00:33:25,405 --> 00:33:26,475
I got a video...

968
00:33:27,305 --> 00:33:28,875
from the members, so I'll take a look.

969
00:33:30,115 --> 00:33:33,415
(He checks the members' mocking video a little late.)

970
00:33:33,745 --> 00:33:37,485
(Doesn't our coffee look tasty?)

971
00:33:37,955 --> 00:33:40,824
(These guys...)

972
00:33:40,825 --> 00:33:42,625
Ki Taek is too nice to tease me.

973
00:33:43,555 --> 00:33:44,725
He didn't take out his tongue.

974
00:33:45,795 --> 00:33:47,594
It's upsetting to see their iced Americano.

975
00:33:47,595 --> 00:33:48,835
(His morale is dropping sharply.)

976
00:33:50,535 --> 00:33:51,635
Let me give it a try.

977
00:33:55,635 --> 00:33:57,504
(Insects for bait)

978
00:33:57,505 --> 00:34:00,605
(Following the AI's advice, he starts by digging the ground.)

979
00:34:03,115 --> 00:34:04,145
I told you.

980
00:34:05,285 --> 00:34:07,184
(As soon as he digs, larvae are everywhere.)

981
00:34:07,185 --> 00:34:08,185
This is amazing.

982
00:34:09,185 --> 00:34:10,215
Unbelievable.

983
00:34:10,885 --> 00:34:12,855
Look, it's alive. Director, take a look at this.

984
00:34:13,455 --> 00:34:14,855
Its legs are moving.

985
00:34:16,095 --> 00:34:17,624
Look at this. It works.

986
00:34:17,625 --> 00:34:18,895
(It really works.)

987
00:34:19,025 --> 00:34:20,795
I dug the ground, and look what I found.

988
00:34:21,135 --> 00:34:22,865
I should put them together.

989
00:34:23,565 --> 00:34:24,565
Let's see.

990
00:34:25,635 --> 00:34:27,905
How did you end up getting caught by me?

991
00:34:28,435 --> 00:34:29,875
See? I got it right away.

992
00:34:31,005 --> 00:34:32,345
- As soon as you started.
- Yes.

993
00:34:33,005 --> 00:34:34,005
Look at this.

994
00:34:34,145 --> 00:34:36,975
Hey, you little thing.

995
00:34:37,985 --> 00:34:39,115
You know...

996
00:34:39,785 --> 00:34:41,415
that it's high in protein, right?

997
00:34:42,815 --> 00:34:44,014
(Thinking hard)

998
00:34:44,015 --> 00:34:45,685
Director Young Jin,

999
00:34:46,125 --> 00:34:47,185
I'll let you have it.

1000
00:34:48,425 --> 00:34:49,994
I'm willing to let you have it.

1001
00:34:49,995 --> 00:34:51,464
(Team Yong Jin even shares an insect.)

1002
00:34:51,465 --> 00:34:53,264
Look, it's actually hard to find them.

1003
00:34:53,265 --> 00:34:55,465
(Look, it's actually hard to find them.)

1004
00:34:55,665 --> 00:34:57,034
How did I find it anyway?

1005
00:34:57,035 --> 00:34:58,735
(Excited, he digs up some more.)

1006
00:34:59,365 --> 00:35:02,434
(No matter how much he digs,)

1007
00:35:02,435 --> 00:35:05,375
(no more insects appear.)

1008
00:35:06,575 --> 00:35:09,615
(Giving up)

1009
00:35:10,075 --> 00:35:13,415
(One insect isn't nearly enough for fishing.)

1010
00:35:13,715 --> 00:35:16,215
What should I do with this rope?

1011
00:35:18,525 --> 00:35:23,825
(Yong Jin is deep in thought for a while.)

1012
00:35:24,125 --> 00:35:25,424
All right.

1013
00:35:25,425 --> 00:35:27,094
(A few minutes later)

1014
00:35:27,095 --> 00:35:28,835
Aren't we teammates today?

1015
00:35:29,235 --> 00:35:32,605
I figured out a way with this rope.

1016
00:35:33,265 --> 00:35:36,675
It's a rope of 10m or 20m.

1017
00:35:37,675 --> 00:35:39,574
- A shelter.
- A shelter?

1018
00:35:39,575 --> 00:35:41,644
It's enough to build a shelter.

1019
00:35:41,645 --> 00:35:44,385
This space right here is suitable...

1020
00:35:44,515 --> 00:35:46,015
for building a shelter.

1021
00:35:46,585 --> 00:35:47,585
All right.

1022
00:35:47,586 --> 00:35:50,584
(So the shelter-building begins.)

1023
00:35:50,585 --> 00:35:52,025
Whose idea was the rope?

1024
00:35:53,625 --> 00:35:55,855
I'm really curious.

1025
00:35:57,355 --> 00:36:00,995
(He starts wrapping the rope between the trees.)

1026
00:36:05,305 --> 00:36:06,464
Like this...

1027
00:36:06,465 --> 00:36:09,104
(He seems to have a plan in mind.)

1028
00:36:09,105 --> 00:36:10,505
To block the sunlight.

1029
00:36:12,005 --> 00:36:13,345
Could you hand me the shovel?

1030
00:36:15,015 --> 00:36:19,785
(He doesn't have a knife, so he cuts the rope with a shovel.)

1031
00:36:20,345 --> 00:36:26,055
(Once it's tightly secured)

1032
00:36:26,755 --> 00:36:27,755
It's done.

1033
00:36:28,425 --> 00:36:31,095
(A roughly 3.3m² space is formed among the trees.)

1034
00:36:31,195 --> 00:36:32,265
Here's my goal.

1035
00:36:32,795 --> 00:36:34,335
Do you see that board way over there?

1036
00:36:35,035 --> 00:36:37,835
(An old discarded board)

1037
00:36:38,705 --> 00:36:40,065
I'm going to put that on top...

1038
00:36:40,605 --> 00:36:43,074
to create a shelter here.

1039
00:36:43,075 --> 00:36:44,175
(He plans to create a shaded shelter with a roof.)

1040
00:36:44,375 --> 00:36:45,375
To put it up...

1041
00:36:45,376 --> 00:36:46,444
(Let's see.)

1042
00:36:46,445 --> 00:36:47,975
It should be tied from here to there.

1043
00:36:48,215 --> 00:36:49,575
In the middle.

1044
00:36:50,715 --> 00:36:53,945
(Material procurement by Lee Yong Jin)

1045
00:36:54,515 --> 00:36:57,925
(Construction by Lee Yong Jin)

1046
00:36:58,185 --> 00:37:02,195
(Everything is done with Yong Jin's own hands.)

1047
00:37:02,895 --> 00:37:03,895
There we go.

1048
00:37:03,896 --> 00:37:06,224
(Construction by Yong Jin, of Yong Jin, and for Yong Jin)

1049
00:37:06,225 --> 00:37:07,395
What are you waiting for? Carry it.

1050
00:37:08,565 --> 00:37:09,994
It's a shelter for both of us.

1051
00:37:09,995 --> 00:37:11,535
- I have to participate?
- Of course.

1052
00:37:11,705 --> 00:37:13,804
We just need to put it up neatly.

1053
00:37:13,805 --> 00:37:15,934
- Do you see where it goes?
- Yes.

1054
00:37:15,935 --> 00:37:17,035
- Right there?
- Yes.

1055
00:37:17,645 --> 00:37:21,575
(They place a perfectly sized board on top.)

1056
00:37:22,215 --> 00:37:27,755
(Once it's fixed securely so that it doesn't fall)

1057
00:37:28,115 --> 00:37:31,925
(A comfortable shaded shelter is complete.)

1058
00:37:32,225 --> 00:37:33,725
It's really fresh here.

1059
00:37:34,725 --> 00:37:35,824
- Is it?
- Yes.

1060
00:37:35,825 --> 00:37:36,925
Go ahead and sit here.

1061
00:37:37,125 --> 00:37:38,425
It feels really fresh.

1062
00:37:39,125 --> 00:37:40,195
You can feel it.

1063
00:37:41,495 --> 00:37:43,265
- Gosh, it's nice and fresh.
- Right.

1064
00:37:43,395 --> 00:37:45,234
- It's really fresh.
- There's some wind too.

1065
00:37:45,235 --> 00:37:46,304
Yes.

1066
00:37:46,305 --> 00:37:48,334
(A comfortable shelter built three hours after being stranded...)

1067
00:37:48,335 --> 00:37:50,404
(on the deserted island)

1068
00:37:50,405 --> 00:37:53,775
I'm not afraid of anything else.

1069
00:37:55,115 --> 00:37:57,985
Once it gets built...

1070
00:37:59,015 --> 00:38:02,054
The moment when I sit underneath over the box of milk.

1071
00:38:02,055 --> 00:38:04,755
That's what I was afraid of the most.

1072
00:38:05,285 --> 00:38:06,755
What do I do now?

1073
00:38:06,885 --> 00:38:08,024
(Laughing)

1074
00:38:08,025 --> 00:38:09,924
I'm afraid of not knowing what to do.

1075
00:38:09,925 --> 00:38:12,325
I was even afraid of completing this.

1076
00:38:12,525 --> 00:38:15,435
The thought of not knowing what to do when I finish this.

1077
00:38:15,595 --> 00:38:17,264
I tried to take my time making it.

1078
00:38:17,265 --> 00:38:19,565
I even thought about cutting the rope to buy time.

1079
00:38:20,335 --> 00:38:24,005
(Seriously, what do I do now?)

1080
00:38:24,905 --> 00:38:27,544
Shall I tie the rope to the pull-up bar...

1081
00:38:27,545 --> 00:38:28,674
and make a swing?

1082
00:38:28,675 --> 00:38:29,745
(Laughing)

1083
00:38:30,545 --> 00:38:32,144
A swing actually sounds nice.

1084
00:38:32,145 --> 00:38:35,307
(Please get me out of here!)

1085
00:38:35,326 --> 00:38:36,798
Everyone, did you have a good time?

1086
00:38:36,829 --> 00:38:39,398
- Yes.
- Ki Taek wanted to say something.

1087
00:38:39,399 --> 00:38:40,728
- What was it?
- Remember?

1088
00:38:40,729 --> 00:38:42,168
I was wondering...

1089
00:38:42,169 --> 00:38:44,208
if we were doing a mission for food.

1090
00:38:44,209 --> 00:38:46,338
The trekking was amazing,

1091
00:38:46,339 --> 00:38:47,839
but I'm starving.

1092
00:38:48,009 --> 00:38:49,508
If kind Ki Taek is bringing it up,

1093
00:38:49,509 --> 00:38:50,678
- it's like he's cursing.
- Right.

1094
00:38:50,679 --> 00:38:52,148
He doesn't usually talk about it.

1095
00:38:52,149 --> 00:38:54,079
- Are we eating soon?
- You're so nice with your words.

1096
00:38:54,319 --> 00:38:55,579
You should say, "Give me food."

1097
00:38:55,919 --> 00:38:59,288
All right, let's continue with your trip.

1098
00:38:59,289 --> 00:39:00,518
- Okay.
- I hope that it goes well.

1099
00:39:00,519 --> 00:39:01,718
I'm afraid that one person will get sent soon.

1100
00:39:01,719 --> 00:39:02,719
- Goodness.
- I have a bad feeling about it.

1101
00:39:02,720 --> 00:39:05,028
Please take one each.

1102
00:39:05,029 --> 00:39:06,289
- I have an ominous feeling.
- Here it is.

1103
00:39:06,459 --> 00:39:07,898
Won't it be resentful to leave now?

1104
00:39:07,899 --> 00:39:08,928
Exactly.

1105
00:39:08,929 --> 00:39:11,028
If you leave now, you won't get to enjoy any luxury.

1106
00:39:11,029 --> 00:39:12,568
We're probably getting food next.

1107
00:39:12,569 --> 00:39:13,569
(We need to eat before we go.)

1108
00:39:13,570 --> 00:39:14,598
- Here you go.
- It's a meal.

1109
00:39:14,599 --> 00:39:16,038
Please.

1110
00:39:16,039 --> 00:39:17,198
I want to keep traveling.

1111
00:39:17,199 --> 00:39:19,638
Everyone, I handed out sketchbooks.

1112
00:39:19,639 --> 00:39:20,738
- Yes.
- Yes.

1113
00:39:20,739 --> 00:39:23,879
From number 1 to 10,

1114
00:39:24,479 --> 00:39:25,778
write down five numbers.

1115
00:39:25,779 --> 00:39:27,009
- Five?
- Yes.

1116
00:39:27,719 --> 00:39:30,519
(Why write numbers all of a sudden?)

1117
00:39:30,679 --> 00:39:32,188
Up to ten?

1118
00:39:32,189 --> 00:39:33,818
- From number 1 to 10, - Up to 10.

1119
00:39:33,819 --> 00:39:35,588
please write down five numbers.

1120
00:39:35,589 --> 00:39:36,958
- Okay.
- From 1 to 10.

1121
00:39:36,959 --> 00:39:38,888
(Choosing carefully)

1122
00:39:38,889 --> 00:39:40,458
My fate depends on it. Let's see.

1123
00:39:40,459 --> 00:39:44,159
(This may determine our fate.)

1124
00:39:44,899 --> 00:39:46,998
(They pick their numbers carefully without knowing why.)

1125
00:39:46,999 --> 00:39:48,069
I wrote them down.

1126
00:39:49,539 --> 00:39:51,368
(Glancing)

1127
00:39:51,369 --> 00:39:52,608
I took a quick look, and I saw nine.

1128
00:39:52,609 --> 00:39:56,709
(You wrote 9.)

1129
00:39:57,039 --> 00:39:59,578
(Cheating Ki Taek)

1130
00:39:59,579 --> 00:40:00,649
I wrote them down.

1131
00:40:01,149 --> 00:40:02,779
- Are you done writing them?
- Yes.

1132
00:40:02,819 --> 00:40:04,349
Now, we'll start...

1133
00:40:04,619 --> 00:40:07,719
- the second check-in mission.
- This is crazy.

1134
00:40:08,389 --> 00:40:09,589
We'll find out the second one to go.

1135
00:40:09,759 --> 00:40:11,458
(This mission will decide who goes to the deserted island.)

1136
00:40:11,459 --> 00:40:12,688
- If you go there now, - No way.

1137
00:40:12,689 --> 00:40:14,328
it could be worse for you than Yong Jin.

1138
00:40:14,329 --> 00:40:16,029
- After doing all the trekking.
- Exactly.

1139
00:40:16,129 --> 00:40:18,498
The second mission to decide who gets stranded...

1140
00:40:18,499 --> 00:40:19,899
on the deserted island is...

1141
00:40:20,029 --> 00:40:22,839
Deserted Island Lottery.

1142
00:40:23,239 --> 00:40:26,408
We received in advance five numbers from Yong Jin...

1143
00:40:26,409 --> 00:40:29,238
who's on the deserted island.

1144
00:40:29,239 --> 00:40:31,609
(5 numbers from Yong Jin received in advance)

1145
00:40:32,149 --> 00:40:33,579
Yong Jin.

1146
00:40:33,649 --> 00:40:36,249
Tell me 5 numbers from 1 to 10.

1147
00:40:39,649 --> 00:40:40,719
Can I leave now?

1148
00:40:42,159 --> 00:40:43,419
Here's what's important.

1149
00:40:44,019 --> 00:40:46,259
The one whose numbers match...

1150
00:40:46,659 --> 00:40:49,199
Yong Jin's numbers the least...

1151
00:40:49,659 --> 00:40:52,428
will check in to the deserted island immediately.

1152
00:40:52,429 --> 00:40:53,698
- Many of them have to match?
- The least?

1153
00:40:53,699 --> 00:40:54,768
Many of them have to match his.

1154
00:40:54,769 --> 00:40:56,599
- This is terrible.
- Goodness.

1155
00:40:56,799 --> 00:40:58,538
- I'm tired of this.
- Please.

1156
00:40:58,539 --> 00:40:59,668
Please.

1157
00:40:59,669 --> 00:41:01,579
Getting three numbers right is enough to play it safe.

1158
00:41:02,009 --> 00:41:04,848
I've won third prize in the lottery before.

1159
00:41:04,849 --> 00:41:06,478
- Really?
- I'm lucky with things like this.

1160
00:41:06,479 --> 00:41:08,218
- I've won third prize too.
- Really?

1161
00:41:08,219 --> 00:41:09,849
- Then we'll be fine.
- Here we go.

1162
00:41:11,219 --> 00:41:12,488
I'll call out the numbers.

1163
00:41:12,489 --> 00:41:14,689
- Please let them match.
- My goodness.

1164
00:41:14,819 --> 00:41:16,518
Why did you write ten?

1165
00:41:16,519 --> 00:41:17,618
He wrote number ten.

1166
00:41:17,619 --> 00:41:18,859
- Number ten is possible.
- Really?

1167
00:41:20,829 --> 00:41:22,758
- He said up to number ten.
- Is that right?

1168
00:41:22,759 --> 00:41:23,799
All right.

1169
00:41:23,859 --> 00:41:25,328
One of them might be ten.

1170
00:41:25,329 --> 00:41:26,369
Please.

1171
00:41:26,629 --> 00:41:28,098
- What's the first number?
- All right.

1172
00:41:28,099 --> 00:41:29,099
(Just how in sync are the members with Yong Jin?)

1173
00:41:29,100 --> 00:41:30,138
Please.

1174
00:41:30,139 --> 00:41:32,438
- The first number is...
- Please.

1175
00:41:32,439 --> 00:41:33,768
Please let it match.

1176
00:41:33,769 --> 00:41:34,838
One.

1177
00:41:34,839 --> 00:41:36,509
Please let it match.

1178
00:41:38,249 --> 00:41:39,379
Seven.

1179
00:41:40,849 --> 00:41:41,918
(Nervous)

1180
00:41:41,919 --> 00:41:42,919
Seven.

1181
00:41:46,989 --> 00:41:48,458
Lee Yong Jin.

1182
00:41:48,459 --> 00:41:50,989
- Lee Yong Jin.
- Lee Yong Jin.

1183
00:41:51,089 --> 00:41:52,488
Lee Yong Jin.

1184
00:41:52,489 --> 00:41:55,158
(Jong Min and Joon lose starting with the first number.)

1185
00:41:55,159 --> 00:41:56,398
Seven...

1186
00:41:56,399 --> 00:41:58,598
- It's not over yet.
- Is it seven?

1187
00:41:58,599 --> 00:42:00,029
(Becoming one with Yong Jin to increase the chances)

1188
00:42:00,369 --> 00:42:01,498
The next number is...

1189
00:42:01,499 --> 00:42:02,539
(The second winning number)

1190
00:42:03,199 --> 00:42:04,199
The next number is...

1191
00:42:04,200 --> 00:42:05,439
(I'd hate to go to the deserted island.)

1192
00:42:05,609 --> 00:42:06,638
(1st edition: 7)

1193
00:42:06,639 --> 00:42:07,739
Three.

1194
00:42:08,179 --> 00:42:09,179
Three.

1195
00:42:11,649 --> 00:42:13,379
(I won again.)

1196
00:42:13,649 --> 00:42:15,419
(Everyone is becoming one with Yong Jin.)

1197
00:42:16,279 --> 00:42:18,149
(This time, Joon also won.)

1198
00:42:19,549 --> 00:42:21,558
(Relieved)

1199
00:42:21,559 --> 00:42:23,358
With one more matching number, I'll be safe. Please.

1200
00:42:23,359 --> 00:42:24,459
I got one right.

1201
00:42:24,929 --> 00:42:26,258
Three.

1202
00:42:26,259 --> 00:42:28,058
(Se Yoon takes the lead.)

1203
00:42:28,059 --> 00:42:30,298
If all my five numbers match his,

1204
00:42:30,299 --> 00:42:31,868
- Yes?
- will there be a present?

1205
00:42:31,869 --> 00:42:33,268
- He'd deserve a present.
- I'm asking just in case.

1206
00:42:33,269 --> 00:42:34,538
- If all your numbers match his, - Right.

1207
00:42:34,539 --> 00:42:35,799
Yong Jin will give you his autograph.

1208
00:42:37,039 --> 00:42:39,508
(I don't need that.)

1209
00:42:39,509 --> 00:42:41,108
All right, the next number is...

1210
00:42:41,109 --> 00:42:42,579
(The third winning number)

1211
00:42:43,079 --> 00:42:44,449
(Please!)

1212
00:42:44,649 --> 00:42:45,708
Five?

1213
00:42:45,709 --> 00:42:46,709
Five.

1214
00:42:49,079 --> 00:42:51,489
(A single number brings cheers and heartbreak.)

1215
00:42:52,189 --> 00:42:53,719
What is Yong Jin up to?

1216
00:42:53,819 --> 00:42:55,319
Five.

1217
00:42:55,959 --> 00:42:56,959
Five.

1218
00:42:56,960 --> 00:42:59,158
(Joon is quietly staying in the game.)

1219
00:42:59,159 --> 00:43:01,999
(Muted cheers)

1220
00:43:03,029 --> 00:43:04,159
Oh, my.

1221
00:43:04,499 --> 00:43:06,129
Look, Joon had it too.

1222
00:43:06,329 --> 00:43:09,199
Yong Jin, I'm your subordinate.

1223
00:43:09,899 --> 00:43:11,208
He picked only odd numbers.

1224
00:43:11,209 --> 00:43:13,009
(Meanwhile, DinDin is the only one in last place.)

1225
00:43:13,209 --> 00:43:15,109
What if he picked 1, 3, 5, 7, and 9?

1226
00:43:15,739 --> 00:43:17,009
No, that can't happen.

1227
00:43:18,379 --> 00:43:20,249
- The next number.
- Please, I need one more.

1228
00:43:20,649 --> 00:43:22,149
- Nine.
- Please.

1229
00:43:23,649 --> 00:43:24,718
Ten.

1230
00:43:24,719 --> 00:43:25,788
(The 1st Edition: 7, 3, 5, 10)

1231
00:43:25,789 --> 00:43:28,218
- Ten.
- Okay.

1232
00:43:28,219 --> 00:43:29,488
Okay.

1233
00:43:29,489 --> 00:43:30,759
(Only the 2 of them wrote 10.)

1234
00:43:31,329 --> 00:43:32,428
(I'd have written 10 if I knew it was possible.)

1235
00:43:32,429 --> 00:43:33,589
Did he pick ten?

1236
00:43:35,459 --> 00:43:38,069
He turned the tables. He really did.

1237
00:43:38,299 --> 00:43:40,468
The 3 of us got 2 matching numbers.

1238
00:43:40,469 --> 00:43:41,798
The 2 of you got 3 matching ones?

1239
00:43:41,799 --> 00:43:43,338
- I got only two.
- All of you?

1240
00:43:43,339 --> 00:43:44,568
- The 4 of us got 2 numbers.
- The 4 of us got 2.

1241
00:43:44,569 --> 00:43:46,168
The next one will decide the winner.

1242
00:43:46,169 --> 00:43:47,838
- Joon, do you have three?
- Yes.

1243
00:43:47,839 --> 00:43:49,739
You're definitely exempt from it.

1244
00:43:49,879 --> 00:43:51,038
- Four numbers.
- We have four numbers so far.

1245
00:43:51,039 --> 00:43:52,208
- The game might get extended.
- We need one more.

1246
00:43:52,209 --> 00:43:53,478
Please, Yong Jin.

1247
00:43:53,479 --> 00:43:55,218
If there are ties, will all of us get dragged?

1248
00:43:55,219 --> 00:43:56,248
(If there are many ties, will they all go?)

1249
00:43:56,249 --> 00:43:58,218
- We'll see. All right.
- Please.

1250
00:43:58,219 --> 00:43:59,718
- All of you will go.
- Please.

1251
00:43:59,719 --> 00:44:01,258
I need to get this right so that I'm excluded.

1252
00:44:01,259 --> 00:44:03,889
- This is the last number.
- Please!

1253
00:44:05,029 --> 00:44:06,029
Please.

1254
00:44:06,289 --> 00:44:07,429
- The last number is...
- Let it be even.

1255
00:44:07,559 --> 00:44:09,729
(What will be the result?)

1256
00:44:10,129 --> 00:44:12,999
(Which one of them will join lonely Yong Jin?)

1257
00:44:13,169 --> 00:44:14,538
Three, five, seven, nine, ten.

1258
00:44:14,539 --> 00:44:16,599
(The last number is 9.)

1259
00:44:17,239 --> 00:44:18,309
Nine.

1260
00:44:19,769 --> 00:44:22,138
(Ki Taek and Jong Min barely survive.)

1261
00:44:22,139 --> 00:44:24,678
- I got three.
- I won.

1262
00:44:24,679 --> 00:44:26,208
- I feel dizzy.
- I got three.

1263
00:44:26,209 --> 00:44:28,978
(His energy level is the highest ever.)

1264
00:44:28,979 --> 00:44:29,979
Nine.

1265
00:44:30,079 --> 00:44:32,388
(With only 2 matching numbers, Se Yoon and DinDin are...)

1266
00:44:32,389 --> 00:44:38,488
(the final candidates for the deserted island.)

1267
00:44:38,489 --> 00:44:41,458
- Three numbers.
- We got three.

1268
00:44:41,459 --> 00:44:42,858
(We don't have to go to the deserted island, right?)

1269
00:44:42,859 --> 00:44:44,199
This is incredible.

1270
00:44:44,529 --> 00:44:47,029
I really don't think Yong Jin and I get along well.

1271
00:44:47,369 --> 00:44:49,839
Se Yoon and DinDin are selected.

1272
00:44:50,039 --> 00:44:52,668
What's the bonus number?

1273
00:44:52,669 --> 00:44:54,369
Bonus number.

1274
00:44:54,739 --> 00:44:57,979
As only one of you will check in,

1275
00:44:58,449 --> 00:45:00,848
we'll get one bonus number.

1276
00:45:00,849 --> 00:45:03,378
What numbers do you have that are different from mine?

1277
00:45:03,379 --> 00:45:05,148
I have 1, 2, and 4. What about you?

1278
00:45:05,149 --> 00:45:06,389
I have 1, 2, 8.

1279
00:45:07,489 --> 00:45:10,359
- If it's 4...
- If it's 4 or 8, it'll be decided.

1280
00:45:10,589 --> 00:45:12,128
Ask him to pick between 4 and 8.

1281
00:45:12,129 --> 00:45:13,129
- Shall I?
- Yes.

1282
00:45:13,130 --> 00:45:14,859
- That would be better.
- All right.

1283
00:45:14,959 --> 00:45:16,858
We'll ask him to choose between the two.

1284
00:45:16,859 --> 00:45:17,899
Eight!

1285
00:45:18,299 --> 00:45:20,868
It'd be fun to watch DinDin with Yong Jin.

1286
00:45:20,869 --> 00:45:23,238
I don't want to be alone with Yong Jin.

1287
00:45:23,239 --> 00:45:24,608
You don't?

1288
00:45:24,609 --> 00:45:26,738
He'll keep scolding me.

1289
00:45:26,739 --> 00:45:28,608
- All right.
- That'd be so fun to watch.

1290
00:45:28,609 --> 00:45:30,379
- Everyone.
- He might get to choose.

1291
00:45:31,039 --> 00:45:32,348
- Do you hear me?
- Okay.

1292
00:45:32,349 --> 00:45:34,618
- Yes, I hear you.
- All right.

1293
00:45:34,619 --> 00:45:35,719
Yong Jin.

1294
00:45:35,949 --> 00:45:37,419
Yong Jin.

1295
00:45:37,619 --> 00:45:40,289
Why do you sound so excited?

1296
00:45:40,489 --> 00:45:42,089
It's very exciting right now.

1297
00:45:42,589 --> 00:45:43,589
Okay.

1298
