2027
01:10:48,477 --> 01:10:50,416
DinDin has gotten a lot better at four-character idioms.

2028
01:10:50,417 --> 01:10:52,387
It's really a high-end fish.

2029
01:10:53,187 --> 01:10:55,087
- How does it taste?
- How is it different?

2030
01:10:55,487 --> 01:10:57,557
How does it taste? Is it different from a flatfish?

2031
01:10:57,727 --> 01:10:58,756
What's the texture like?

2032
01:10:58,757 --> 01:11:01,657
You can just tell that it's a high-end fish as you chew it.

2033
01:11:01,897 --> 01:11:03,427
- The texture.
- How is it different?

2034
01:11:03,827 --> 01:11:06,667
You can really feel all the texture when you chew it.

2035
01:11:07,737 --> 01:11:10,367
I think it definitely moves more than a flatfish.

2036
01:11:10,707 --> 01:11:12,736
- You can really feel the texture.
- It was strong.

2037
01:11:12,737 --> 01:11:13,877
You can really feel the texture.

2038
01:11:14,007 --> 01:11:16,747
You can't talk about it after just eating one piece.

2039
01:11:17,047 --> 01:11:18,276
You have to just keep eating.

2040
01:11:18,277 --> 01:11:21,317
We should have had a large portion. What a shame.

2041
01:11:21,977 --> 01:11:23,246
He has sliced a lot.

2042
01:11:23,247 --> 01:11:25,247
(He eats some hijiki to comfort himself.)

2043
01:11:25,657 --> 01:11:26,787
Thank you for the food.

2044
01:11:27,987 --> 01:11:29,556
We did quite well, though.

2045
01:11:29,557 --> 01:11:31,027
- That's right.
- We did well.

2046
01:11:31,657 --> 01:11:34,597
Tell us how the other team is doing so we feel better.

2047
01:11:34,697 --> 01:11:36,627
- The other team?
- Are they eating as well?

2048
01:11:37,697 --> 01:11:39,667
We have to eat when they give us food.

2049
01:11:40,237 --> 01:11:41,367
We should eat.

2050
01:11:42,807 --> 01:11:44,036
I guess we can plug this in.

2051
01:11:44,037 --> 01:11:46,337
(They go through the welcome kit before preparing lunch.)

2052
01:11:47,107 --> 01:11:50,807
(Lunch menu on the deserted island: small cup noodles and instant rice)

2053
01:11:51,307 --> 01:11:53,676
(A portable electric kettle and a solar-powered...)

2054
01:11:53,677 --> 01:11:56,087
(rechargeable battery are provided for cooking.)

2055
01:11:56,287 --> 01:11:57,386
You're giving us a battery?

2056
01:11:57,387 --> 01:12:00,117
(The provided solar-powered rechargeable battery...)

2057
01:12:00,687 --> 01:12:04,857
(can be connected to the portable electric kettle to boil water!)

2058
01:12:05,287 --> 01:12:07,927
What do we do if it can't fill two cups?

2059
01:12:08,627 --> 01:12:10,266
I don't like salty noodles.

2060
01:12:10,267 --> 01:12:11,967
(The water would be enough to make 2 cup noodles, right?)

2061
01:12:12,397 --> 01:12:15,197
(He fills the electric kettle with water.)

2062
01:12:15,467 --> 01:12:16,467
Here.

2063
01:12:16,468 --> 01:12:17,906
(Connect the solar-powered battery to the kettle to boil water.)

2064
01:12:17,907 --> 01:12:19,537
Insert it and switch it on.

2065
01:12:20,137 --> 01:12:23,277
Set it to 100°C. It would ring when it's done, right?

2066
01:12:25,917 --> 01:12:27,376
- It's 23°C now.
- Yes. It's going up.

2067
01:12:27,377 --> 01:12:28,477
It's going up.

2068
01:12:29,347 --> 01:12:31,047
This is amazing.

2069
01:12:31,647 --> 01:12:32,856
How do we cook rice?

2070
01:12:32,857 --> 01:12:34,917
- How do we eat rice?
- They're teasing us, aren't they?

2071
01:12:36,157 --> 01:12:37,926
(The electric kettle can only make cup noodles.)

2072
01:12:37,927 --> 01:12:38,987
Let me try a little.

2073
01:12:43,797 --> 01:12:45,527
It's worse than I thought.

2074
01:12:45,737 --> 01:12:47,566
- It's bad.
- It's really horrible.

2075
01:12:47,567 --> 01:12:49,607
- You can't eat that.
- I don't think we can.

2076
01:12:49,967 --> 01:12:51,007
(Sighing)

2077
01:12:51,567 --> 01:12:53,177
I miss the others.

2078
01:12:53,337 --> 01:12:55,077
Don't you have a gas burner here?

2079
01:12:55,437 --> 01:12:57,046
They don't because...

2080
01:12:57,047 --> 01:12:59,147
- you can't cook on the island.
- You can't?

2081
01:12:59,717 --> 01:13:00,746
- You can't use fire.
- No fire?

2082
01:13:00,747 --> 01:13:01,777
- Really?
- There's no solution.

2083
01:13:01,947 --> 01:13:04,547
Why don't we put the rice...

2084
01:13:05,317 --> 01:13:07,616
Should we cook them together?

2085
01:13:07,617 --> 01:13:08,716
(Brainy Yong Jin's solution: Put rice underneath.)

2086
01:13:08,717 --> 01:13:10,557
- I think we could do that.
- Should we really do that?

2087
01:13:10,827 --> 01:13:12,956
- Should we put half the rice?
- Yes. That would be better.

2088
01:13:12,957 --> 01:13:13,997
- Should we do that instead?
- Yes.

2089
01:13:14,097 --> 01:13:15,156
One chunk.

2090
01:13:15,157 --> 01:13:16,626
(Preparing a meal on a deserted island)

2091
01:13:16,627 --> 01:13:18,126
(Place firm instant rice under cup noodles to cook them together.)

2092
01:13:18,127 --> 01:13:19,466
- One chunk.
- That would be perfect.

2093
01:13:19,467 --> 01:13:20,937
Right. Let's put it there.

2094
01:13:21,267 --> 01:13:23,707
Then I'll also...

2095
01:13:24,667 --> 01:13:28,537
(Se Yoon also puts some rice in his cup noodle.)

2096
01:13:29,407 --> 01:13:30,607
Where's the ramyeon seasoning?

2097
01:13:31,277 --> 01:13:32,477
The ramyeon seasoning, Yong Jin.

2098
01:13:35,077 --> 01:13:37,086
- The ramyeon seasoning, Yong Jin.
- You'd know where it is.

2099
01:13:37,087 --> 01:13:38,647
(Se Yoon's ramyeon seasoning is missing!)

2100
01:13:38,747 --> 01:13:39,857
Don't do this, Yong Jin.

2101
01:13:40,757 --> 01:13:42,626
- How many times have I said that?
- I really didn't do it.

2102
01:13:42,627 --> 01:13:43,727
Don't do it.

2103
01:13:44,027 --> 01:13:45,826
Yong Jin. The ramyeon seasoning is really missing.

2104
01:13:45,827 --> 01:13:46,896
(I'm cranky because I'm hungry. Don't joke around.)

2105
01:13:46,897 --> 01:13:48,526
- Yong Jin.
- I really didn't hide it.

2106
01:13:48,527 --> 01:13:50,196
- Yong Jin.
- I really didn't hide it.

2107
01:13:50,197 --> 01:13:51,896
- I'm saying this for the last time.
- Seriously.

2108
01:13:51,897 --> 01:13:54,036
- Yong Jin. You...
- I didn't hide it.

2109
01:13:54,037 --> 01:13:55,736
- I really didn't hide it.
- You really shouldn't do that.

2110
01:13:55,737 --> 01:13:58,066
- I swear to the sky.
- It's here! I'm sorry.

2111
01:13:58,067 --> 01:13:59,607
(He almost picked on the wrong guy.)

2112
01:14:00,307 --> 01:14:02,276
I'm so hungry after the hike.

2113
01:14:02,277 --> 01:14:03,576
(The cup noodles and instant rice are set.)

2114
01:14:03,577 --> 01:14:05,106
- Se Yoon, I...
- Yes?

2115
01:14:05,107 --> 01:14:06,917
Let me have one of the candies. I haven't had anything.

2116
01:14:07,777 --> 01:14:09,746
Me neither. You'll lose your appetite. Would that be okay?

2117
01:14:09,747 --> 01:14:10,847
It's okay.

2118
01:14:11,517 --> 01:14:13,756
We used to drink americanos.

2119
01:14:13,757 --> 01:14:14,817
I know.

2120
01:14:15,757 --> 01:14:16,926
This is good.

2121
01:14:16,927 --> 01:14:18,327
(The worldly sourness hits his taste buds.)

2122
01:14:18,527 --> 01:14:20,656
All I've eaten here is seaweed.

2123
01:14:20,657 --> 01:14:23,096
- When did you eat seaweed?
- I found seaweed at the shore.

2124
01:14:23,097 --> 01:14:26,166
- You just ate it?
- I tasted it, but it didn't help.

2125
01:14:26,167 --> 01:14:27,396
It would have tasted fishy.

2126
01:14:27,397 --> 01:14:28,666
I wouldn't want that even on my birthday.

2127
01:14:28,667 --> 01:14:30,507
(It tasted so fishy that I wouldn't eat it even on my birthday.)

2128
01:14:32,267 --> 01:14:34,737
It's not heating up as fast as I thought.

2129
01:14:35,377 --> 01:14:36,706
Is the battery weak?

2130
01:14:36,707 --> 01:14:38,646
It shouldn't take too long.

2131
01:14:38,647 --> 01:14:41,146
(The kettle is taking so long to boil the water!)

2132
01:14:41,147 --> 01:14:42,987
I'm really hungry right now.

2133
01:14:43,317 --> 01:14:44,387
Hold on.

2134
01:14:44,787 --> 01:14:47,357
Let's find out the minimum of how hot ramyeon water should be.

2135
01:14:48,317 --> 01:14:51,486
- Ramyeon water temperature.
- I believe it's 80°C.

2136
01:14:51,487 --> 01:14:54,096
- Water temperature.
- It's at least 80°C.

2137
01:14:54,097 --> 01:14:55,827
(There's a lot left until it reaches 80°C.)

2138
01:14:56,627 --> 01:15:01,197
(They continue to wait for 20 minutes.)

2139
01:15:01,997 --> 01:15:04,506
(Is it not ready yet?)

2140
01:15:04,507 --> 01:15:07,277
Se Yoon! It's suddenly dropping to 57°C.

2141
01:15:07,507 --> 01:15:08,936
This is driving me mad.

2142
01:15:08,937 --> 01:15:10,306
(Why is it like this all of a sudden?)

2143
01:15:10,307 --> 01:15:12,577
For your information, that's not a portable charger.

2144
01:15:12,947 --> 01:15:13,947
It's a solar charger.

2145
01:15:14,577 --> 01:15:15,917
Must it be flipped over?

2146
01:15:16,147 --> 01:15:17,987
- It must be opened.
- How?

2147
01:15:18,087 --> 01:15:19,116
This must be opened?

2148
01:15:19,117 --> 01:15:21,317
It should be placed under the sunlight.

2149
01:15:21,717 --> 01:15:23,056
Will it boil faster like this?

2150
01:15:23,057 --> 01:15:24,987
It will work much faster under the sunlight.

2151
01:15:25,087 --> 01:15:26,296
It's because I don't want to move.

2152
01:15:26,297 --> 01:15:27,556
- Give it to me.
- Okay.

2153
01:15:27,557 --> 01:15:29,467
Gosh, you should've told us earlier!

2154
01:15:29,527 --> 01:15:31,127
Does it work faster when it's opened?

2155
01:15:31,597 --> 01:15:32,597
Gosh, I'm feeling heartburn.

2156
01:15:32,598 --> 01:15:35,297
(At the thought of having to wait more,)

2157
01:15:35,697 --> 01:15:36,736
Gosh, I'm hungry.

2158
01:15:36,737 --> 01:15:42,547
(he starts to feel heartburn.)

2159
01:15:43,147 --> 01:15:44,977
It will boil faster when placed like this!

2160
01:15:46,917 --> 01:15:48,716
(It's charged from this part.)

2161
01:15:48,717 --> 01:15:50,147
(When spread out under the sunlight...)

2162
01:15:50,487 --> 01:15:51,817
It's 60°C right away.

2163
01:15:51,987 --> 01:15:53,087
- Really?
- Yes.

2164
01:15:54,057 --> 01:15:55,617
Gosh, I'm feeling anemia.

2165
01:15:56,057 --> 01:15:57,427
It's darn hard to have some cup raymeon.

2166
01:16:01,257 --> 01:16:02,896
Gosh, I want some bossam and jokbal.

2167
01:16:02,897 --> 01:16:05,967
(The water boiling has gone back to the start.)

2168
01:16:06,867 --> 01:16:08,066
Let's eat when it's 80°C.

2169
01:16:08,067 --> 01:16:09,806
(Around 40 minutes of water boiling)

2170
01:16:09,807 --> 01:16:10,937
We'll be able to eat when it's 80°C.

2171
01:16:11,667 --> 01:16:13,477
Gosh, it stopped exactly at 78°C!

2172
01:16:13,537 --> 01:16:14,776
This is fine. We'll be able to eat.

2173
01:16:14,777 --> 01:16:16,706
We'll be able to eat. Okay. Get ready.

2174
01:16:16,707 --> 01:16:18,576
(Let's eat.)

2175
01:16:18,577 --> 01:16:19,677
Let's eat.

2176
01:16:19,777 --> 01:16:21,546
- Let's start.
- Go first.

2177
01:16:21,547 --> 01:16:23,387
- Thank you.
- Go first.

2178
01:16:23,747 --> 01:16:25,346
I see the smoke.

2179
01:16:25,347 --> 01:16:26,857
- You do?
- Yes. I see the smoke.

2180
01:16:27,417 --> 01:16:29,186
- I can slightly see it.
- I see the smoke.

2181
01:16:29,187 --> 01:16:30,227
You should stop now.

2182
01:16:30,757 --> 01:16:33,227
- Stop!
- I'm done.

2183
01:16:33,457 --> 01:16:34,897
Why would you fill it to the top?

2184
01:16:34,957 --> 01:16:36,027
Fine.

2185
01:16:37,397 --> 01:16:38,497
It's more than enough.

2186
01:16:38,697 --> 01:16:40,237
Just a little more.

2187
01:16:41,637 --> 01:16:43,106
I'm sorry, Yong Jin!

2188
01:16:43,107 --> 01:16:44,236
(They get sensitive with water as they are short on supplies.)

2189
01:16:44,237 --> 01:16:45,267
It's filled.

2190
01:16:45,537 --> 01:16:47,876
- Four minutes.
- It must never be opened.

2191
01:16:47,877 --> 01:16:50,307
(It takes 4 minutes to cook.)

2192
01:16:51,277 --> 01:16:52,617
My stomach is going wild.

2193
01:16:52,877 --> 01:16:54,117
It keeps growling.

2194
01:16:55,777 --> 01:16:56,846
Gosh, I'm hungry.

2195
01:16:56,847 --> 01:16:58,286
(After another time of wait...)

2196
01:16:58,287 --> 01:16:59,857
Around five minutes passed.

2197
01:16:59,987 --> 01:17:01,317
- Will you check?
- I'll check first.

2198
01:17:01,657 --> 01:17:03,157
Poke it with the chopsticks.

2199
01:17:03,257 --> 01:17:05,127
- Please go in.
- Please. It must go straight in.

2200
01:17:05,387 --> 01:17:07,697
- It must go in.
- Break through the rice.

2201
01:17:08,957 --> 01:17:10,566
- Gosh, it's going in!
- Gosh, it's going in!

2202
01:17:10,567 --> 01:17:11,896
- It's going in.
- Okay.

2203
01:17:11,897 --> 01:17:13,567
We had a lot of water.

2204
01:17:13,997 --> 01:17:15,467
The rice isn't cooked.

2205
01:17:15,537 --> 01:17:17,366
- The rice isn't cooked?
- It isn't cooked at all.

2206
01:17:17,367 --> 01:17:19,136
- It must be mixed.
- It isn't cooked at all.

2207
01:17:19,137 --> 01:17:20,206
(It's hard to cook rice with 80°C water.)

2208
01:17:20,207 --> 01:17:21,306
It isn't cooked at all.

2209
01:17:21,307 --> 01:17:22,376
(Se Yoon also tries poking it with his chopsticks.)

2210
01:17:22,377 --> 01:17:23,377
The rice is...

2211
01:17:24,207 --> 01:17:25,576
- The rice isn't cooked.
- The rice...

2212
01:17:25,577 --> 01:17:27,676
- I can't go through the rice.
- It feels like sand.

2213
01:17:27,677 --> 01:17:29,486
The rice blocks the chopsticks.

2214
01:17:29,487 --> 01:17:30,987
(Hard)

2215
01:17:33,457 --> 01:17:35,817
(It even bounces off.)

2216
01:17:36,187 --> 01:17:38,557
(Let's still have our first precious meal on the deserted island.)

2217
01:17:40,527 --> 01:17:41,696
(A small and precious bite of ramyeon)

2218
01:17:41,697 --> 01:17:42,767
How is it? Is it okay?

2219
01:17:43,627 --> 01:17:45,367
- Is it okay?
- The noodles are cooked.

2220
01:17:46,937 --> 01:17:50,107
(He picks up a lot with his chopsticks.)

2221
01:17:51,237 --> 01:17:54,207
(Satisfied)

2222
01:17:56,877 --> 01:18:00,077
(The small cup ramyeon gets finished with two bites.)

2223
01:18:00,847 --> 01:18:02,477
The noodles are nice.

2224
01:18:02,617 --> 01:18:03,817
The noodles are fine.

2225
01:18:04,647 --> 01:18:06,486
(The 45-minute wait was worth it.)

2226
01:18:06,487 --> 01:18:08,417
The noodles are fine. The rice is the problem.

2227
01:18:09,257 --> 01:18:12,357
(He tries the uncooked rice this time.)

2228
01:18:13,197 --> 01:18:15,027
The rice can't be chewed.

2229
01:18:15,897 --> 01:18:16,967
The rice can't be chewed.

2230
01:18:17,367 --> 01:18:20,797
Ramyeon rice should spread out like sikhye.

2231
01:18:21,237 --> 01:18:23,867
(I can't have this no matter how hungry I am.)

2232
01:18:24,337 --> 01:18:26,677
(Chewing uncooked rice)

2233
01:18:27,077 --> 01:18:29,136
- We still have to eat it.
- It can't be chewed.

2234
01:18:29,137 --> 01:18:30,447
We have to survive.

2235
01:18:30,677 --> 01:18:32,607
It's too hard.

2236
01:18:32,817 --> 01:18:33,877
Think that it was fried.

2237
01:18:35,677 --> 01:18:38,187
(Slurping)

2238
01:18:39,487 --> 01:18:43,257
(Yong Jin drinks the soup although the rice made it hard.)

2239
01:18:43,457 --> 01:18:44,687
- Did you finish it?
- Yes.

2240
01:18:44,887 --> 01:18:46,656
You were never someone who would finish the soup.

2241
01:18:46,657 --> 01:18:47,657
I finished it.

2242
01:18:48,097 --> 01:18:49,627
What do we do now?

2243
01:18:50,367 --> 01:18:52,566
- What do you want to do?
- I'm not sure.

2244
01:18:52,567 --> 01:18:53,837
(I don't know what to do after staying here for 4 hours.)

2245
01:18:54,467 --> 01:18:56,167
Should we see if there's any food here?

2246
01:18:56,267 --> 01:18:57,337
There's nothing here.

2247
01:18:57,537 --> 01:18:59,306
There are conches. Let's catch conches.

2248
01:18:59,307 --> 01:19:00,777
- Are there no murexes?
- There are conches.

2249
01:19:01,107 --> 01:19:02,536
Should we go for a walk?

2250
01:19:02,537 --> 01:19:03,746
- Sure.
- What can we do here?

2251
01:19:03,747 --> 01:19:05,607
- Let's digest our food.
- Right.

2252
01:19:06,677 --> 01:19:08,316
Is there nothing we can catch here?

2253
01:19:08,317 --> 01:19:09,317
(Will they be able to find food?)

2254
01:19:09,318 --> 01:19:11,116
- Where are the conches?
- They're over there.

2255
01:19:11,117 --> 01:19:12,147
There?

2256
01:19:12,987 --> 01:19:14,017
If you look there...

2257
01:19:15,087 --> 01:19:17,387
- Where? I don't see any.
- Where have they gone?

2258
01:19:17,927 --> 01:19:19,457
You're talking about the ones down there.

2259
01:19:19,957 --> 01:19:21,926
There were a lot earlier.

2260
01:19:21,927 --> 01:19:24,267
They went down as the water came up!

2261
01:19:25,127 --> 01:19:27,836
They must've moved away.

2262
01:19:27,837 --> 01:19:30,066
Right. They went down as the water came up.

2263
01:19:30,067 --> 01:19:31,207
Gosh.

2264
01:19:31,807 --> 01:19:32,807
It's a crab.

2265
01:19:33,407 --> 01:19:35,177
It's a crab, Yong Jin!

2266
01:19:36,147 --> 01:19:37,806
- Can you catch it?
- Yes. Where is it?

2267
01:19:37,807 --> 01:19:39,376
(They try to catch it.)

2268
01:19:39,377 --> 01:19:40,517
You can catch crabs.

2269
01:19:41,647 --> 01:19:43,246
Gosh, it broke off! I'm sorry.

2270
01:19:43,247 --> 01:19:45,847
(They miss the crab.)

2271
01:19:45,947 --> 01:19:47,257
There's nothing here.

2272
01:19:47,487 --> 01:19:49,156
- Se Yoon!
- Yes?

2273
01:19:49,157 --> 01:19:50,727
Take a look at this. I think it's a sea cucumber.

2274
01:19:50,927 --> 01:19:52,557
- What are you saying?
- I'm serious.

2275
01:19:53,227 --> 01:19:55,156
Liar. It's not a sea cucumber.

2276
01:19:55,157 --> 01:19:56,326
It's not a sea cucumber.

2277
01:19:56,327 --> 01:19:58,667
It's something else. Why would they be here?

2278
01:19:59,397 --> 01:20:00,797
There's nothing to eat!

2279
01:20:03,007 --> 01:20:04,207
There's nothing to eat!

2280
01:20:05,037 --> 01:20:06,906
- Gosh, I'm hungry.
- There's nothing at all!

2281
01:20:06,907 --> 01:20:07,907
(The two failed to find food.)

2282
01:20:07,908 --> 01:20:09,007
I'm hungry!

2283
01:20:09,237 --> 01:20:11,146
Let's make a bet with snacks.

2284
01:20:11,147 --> 01:20:12,876
- We have sour candy.
- We have hard candy.

2285
01:20:12,877 --> 01:20:14,077
Hard candy? That sounds great!

2286
01:20:14,617 --> 01:20:16,247
Peanut candy? Is it genuine? Let me take a look.

2287
01:20:16,817 --> 01:20:18,516
- Is it genuine?
- It isn't something else, right?

2288
01:20:18,517 --> 01:20:19,757
Okay.

2289
01:20:19,987 --> 01:20:21,287
How does it sound for me to stay on for 30 seconds?

2290
01:20:21,457 --> 01:20:23,326
- We'll earn 1 for 30 seconds.
- Right.

2291
01:20:23,327 --> 01:20:25,056
- Sounds good. It's 30 seconds.
- For 1.

2292
01:20:25,057 --> 01:20:26,357
I'll be able to hang on for 30 seconds.

2293
01:20:26,757 --> 01:20:28,226
I'll think it's the end of me if I fall.

2294
01:20:28,227 --> 01:20:29,356
I can think that I'm hanging off a cliff.

2295
01:20:29,357 --> 01:20:30,397
Will I not be able to do this?

2296
01:20:30,867 --> 01:20:32,027
A breadwinner is different.

2297
01:20:32,897 --> 01:20:35,567
(It suddenly becomes "Dad's Challenge.")

2298
01:20:35,997 --> 01:20:37,367
Is this the right form? Okay.

2299
01:20:37,437 --> 01:20:39,237
- Get ready.
- I think this is right.

2300
01:20:39,707 --> 01:20:40,977
My hands hurt a bit. Hold on.

2301
01:20:41,177 --> 01:20:44,206
- Gosh.
- Why do you have so many issues?

2302
01:20:44,207 --> 01:20:46,007
- Hold on.
- Come on.

2303
01:20:46,777 --> 01:20:48,047
My hands hurt a bit.

2304
01:20:49,417 --> 01:20:52,216
(I will earn the peanut candy if I hang on for 30 seconds!)

2305
01:20:52,217 --> 01:20:53,287
Let's go!

2306
01:20:53,887 --> 01:20:55,686
(The dad holds the bar tight.)

2307
01:20:55,687 --> 01:20:56,687
Okay.

2308
01:20:56,827 --> 01:20:58,727
I'll set the 30 seconds...

2309
01:20:59,557 --> 01:21:00,996
with the stopwatch.

2310
01:21:00,997 --> 01:21:03,826
I'll choose a nice sound to celebrate.

2311
01:21:03,827 --> 01:21:05,366
(A nice sound will ring after 30 seconds.)

2312
01:21:05,367 --> 01:21:06,667
That sounds bright.

2313
01:21:07,497 --> 01:21:08,537
All right.

2314
01:21:09,067 --> 01:21:10,067
Get ready.

2315
01:21:10,068 --> 01:21:11,206
(Feeling very nervous for a piece of peanut candy)

2316
01:21:11,207 --> 01:21:13,877
Start.

2317
01:21:14,237 --> 01:21:16,346
We did it. It's over.

2318
01:21:16,347 --> 01:21:17,507
Five seconds went by.

2319
01:21:20,577 --> 01:21:23,046
(Peanut candy will be earned if he makes it!)

2320
01:21:23,047 --> 01:21:25,786
(Sour candy will be taken away if he fails!)

2321
01:21:25,787 --> 01:21:26,787
Around 15 seconds.

2322
01:21:27,187 --> 01:21:28,716
I'll think it's the end of me if I fall.

2323
01:21:28,717 --> 01:21:29,756
I can think that I'm hanging off a cliff.

2324
01:21:29,757 --> 01:21:30,786
Will I not be able to do this?

2325
01:21:30,787 --> 01:21:32,526
- Don't move. It'll make it worse.
- I think he'll make it.

2326
01:21:32,527 --> 01:21:33,596
He'll make it.

2327
01:21:33,597 --> 01:21:36,967
(His feet show how desperate he is.)

2328
01:21:37,767 --> 01:21:41,296
- He did it.
- Five, four, three...

2329
01:21:41,297 --> 01:21:43,337
(There are just 5 seconds left.)

2330
01:21:47,637 --> 01:21:48,637
Yes!

2331
01:21:48,977 --> 01:21:52,547
(The bright sound goes off after 30 seconds.)

2332
01:21:52,877 --> 01:21:54,016
Gosh.

2333
01:21:54,017 --> 01:21:55,377
(Se Yoon's pain is unlike the bright sound.)

2334
01:21:55,917 --> 01:21:57,047
(Laughing)

2335
01:21:57,717 --> 01:21:59,147
That was really tough.

2336
01:21:59,687 --> 01:22:01,886
(Moon Se Yoon manages to hold on for 30 seconds.)

2337
01:22:01,887 --> 01:22:03,456
- You made it.
- My hands hurt so much.

2338
01:22:03,457 --> 01:22:04,827
I think my skin peeled off.

2339
01:22:05,157 --> 01:22:06,597
Take my glove off for me.

2340
01:22:06,727 --> 01:22:08,196
I just felt the pain of the underworld.

2341
01:22:08,197 --> 01:22:10,266
(Yong Jin helps him take off his gloves.)

2342
01:22:10,267 --> 01:22:12,527
- My skin peeled off.
- His skin peeled off.

2343
01:22:12,667 --> 01:22:14,136
My skin peeled off.

2344
01:22:14,137 --> 01:22:17,337
(Traces of his struggles)

2345
01:22:17,637 --> 01:22:19,067
Check out my arm. It's firm.

2346
01:22:19,437 --> 01:22:21,277
- Gosh.
- It pumped up my muscles.

2347
01:22:21,577 --> 01:22:24,577
I can beat things like this.

2348
01:22:28,877 --> 01:22:30,816
- The candy.
- Here you are.

2349
01:22:30,817 --> 01:22:32,347
(Please give me the peanut candy now.)

2350
01:22:32,887 --> 01:22:34,657
Thank you. I stayed on for 30 seconds.

2351
01:22:34,787 --> 01:22:35,787
Gosh, I'm sweating so much.

2352
01:22:35,788 --> 01:22:37,157
(All for a piece of candy)

2353
01:22:37,327 --> 01:22:38,356
(Meanwhile, the members on the inhabited island...)

2354
01:22:38,357 --> 01:22:39,387
(have finished eating.)

2355
01:22:40,097 --> 01:22:41,796
- I'd love to stay here.
- It's a rich man's house.

2356
01:22:41,797 --> 01:22:43,727
- It's a tile-roofed house.
- There's a tile-roofed house.

2357
01:22:43,867 --> 01:22:45,267
I hope this place is our base camp.

2358
01:22:45,627 --> 01:22:47,036
This place is great!

2359
01:22:47,037 --> 01:22:48,296
You've all enjoyed the floating party, right?

2360
01:22:48,297 --> 01:22:49,297
- Yes.
- Yes.

2361
01:22:49,298 --> 01:22:51,166
I'm greatly satisfied with the four-man group.

2362
01:22:51,167 --> 01:22:53,506
Right. There are fewer mouths to feed.

2363
01:22:53,507 --> 01:22:54,806
- It's a smaller group.
- There was enough food.

2364
01:22:54,807 --> 01:22:57,376
This place is Geumdang Island's...

2365
01:22:57,377 --> 01:22:59,346
- Chau-ri Village.
- Chau-ri Village?

2366
01:22:59,347 --> 01:23:00,646
- Yes.
- Chau-ri Village.

2367
01:23:00,647 --> 01:23:02,317
- It's a pretty name.
- Chau-ri.

2368
01:23:02,547 --> 01:23:03,986
Right here...

2369
01:23:03,987 --> 01:23:05,147
- Gosh.
- Gosh.

2370
01:23:05,387 --> 01:23:06,687
- There's no place to go from here.
- The third...

2371
01:23:06,887 --> 01:23:09,756
The third deserted island check-in mission...

2372
01:23:09,757 --> 01:23:11,326
- will begin.
- Sir,

2373
01:23:11,327 --> 01:23:13,196
we won't know the limit, right?

2374
01:23:13,197 --> 01:23:15,956
All of us might end up sent away. You won't tell us, right?

2375
01:23:15,957 --> 01:23:17,327
No. You'll have to find out.

2376
01:23:17,867 --> 01:23:19,837
- Ki Taek, you should experience it.
- Right.

2377
01:23:20,037 --> 01:23:22,196
- I had a good meal, - Right.

2378
01:23:22,197 --> 01:23:23,966
so it doesn't really matter if I go.

2379
01:23:23,967 --> 01:23:25,866
- Okay!
- Really? You should go then!

2380
01:23:25,867 --> 01:23:28,036
- But it should be fair and square.
- You should volunteer for it.

2381
01:23:28,037 --> 01:23:29,076
But...

2382
01:23:29,077 --> 01:23:31,246
I should play fair and square until the end.

2383
01:23:31,247 --> 01:23:32,676
Just don't make it seem obvious.

2384
01:23:32,677 --> 01:23:34,247
This mission...

2385
01:23:34,617 --> 01:23:36,686
is called Catch Tail After Tail.

2386
01:23:36,687 --> 01:23:38,086
- Catch Tail After Tail?
- My heart hurts.

2387
01:23:38,087 --> 01:23:40,316
- These games drive me crazy.
- All right.

2388
01:23:40,317 --> 01:23:44,257
You have to get the tail of the same color of your belt.

2389
01:23:44,427 --> 01:23:47,456
Let's say Ki Taek is wearing a red belt.

2390
01:23:47,457 --> 01:23:50,666
- Right.
- You must get the red tail.

2391
01:23:50,667 --> 01:23:52,566
Right. I see.

2392
01:23:52,567 --> 01:23:53,897
I fully got it.

2393
01:23:54,597 --> 01:23:56,266
What happens when there's nothing left?

2394
01:23:56,267 --> 01:23:58,266
The one who has no tail left...

2395
01:23:58,267 --> 01:24:00,637
will check in to the deserted island right at that moment.

2396
01:24:00,907 --> 01:24:03,147
- It's a game of wits.
- This isn't an individual battle.

2397
01:24:03,247 --> 01:24:04,946
- In a way, it's a team game.
- We must help each other.

2398
01:24:04,947 --> 01:24:06,876
- We must help each other.
- Okay. Sounds good.

2399
01:24:06,877 --> 01:24:08,676
- Okay.
- Let's go.

2400
01:24:08,677 --> 01:24:10,816
- Can I hide somewhere?
- We'll use our strength here.

2401
01:24:10,817 --> 01:24:12,017
(Who will be the third member to check in to the deserted island?)

2402
01:24:12,787 --> 01:24:15,257
Lead me far away.

2403
01:24:15,917 --> 01:24:17,826
(The starting positions of the members)

2404
01:24:17,827 --> 01:24:19,957
(Joon, Ki Taek, DinDin, Jong Min)

2405
01:24:20,157 --> 01:24:22,027
So I have to go after yellow first.

2406
01:24:22,827 --> 01:24:24,096
Yellow.

2407
01:24:24,097 --> 01:24:28,297
(Ki Taek can only go after the yellow tail.)

2408
01:24:28,397 --> 01:24:31,706
I must avoid the green belt and go after the yellow tail.

2409
01:24:31,707 --> 01:24:33,037
(He must avoid the member with the green belt.)

2410
01:24:33,207 --> 01:24:34,836
As I must get the yellow tail,

2411
01:24:34,837 --> 01:24:36,877
I hope Jong Min is the one with the yellow tail.

2412
01:24:37,177 --> 01:24:38,977
It's harder for the one who is older.

2413
01:24:39,347 --> 01:24:40,917
I think I'll be able to get his tail.

2414
01:24:41,317 --> 01:24:42,776
I bet he will get tired soon.

2415
01:24:42,777 --> 01:24:44,516
I hope Jong Min has the yellow tail.

2416
01:24:44,517 --> 01:24:45,517
(Will Jong Min's tail be yellow, just as Ki Taek wishes?)

2417
01:24:45,717 --> 01:24:47,887
(Jong Min can pull off only the green tail.)

2418
01:24:48,087 --> 01:24:50,287
Should I wear it around my waist so it shows?

2419
01:24:51,127 --> 01:24:53,297
Once they see my belt, they will know what color I'm after.

2420
01:24:54,297 --> 01:24:56,497
(Contrary to Ki Taek's wish, he has a blue tail.)

2421
01:24:56,597 --> 01:24:58,426
- So I should rip off the blue tail?
- Yes.

2422
01:24:58,427 --> 01:24:59,566
(Lee Joon can pull off only the blue tail.)

2423
01:24:59,567 --> 01:25:02,696
So I must avoid anyone with the red belt.

2424
01:25:02,697 --> 01:25:04,007
- Yes.
- The red belt.

2425
01:25:04,267 --> 01:25:05,806
You should rip off the red tail.

2426
01:25:05,807 --> 01:25:07,937
(DinDin can pull off only the red tail.)

2427
01:25:08,477 --> 01:25:10,807
(He needs to avoid Ki Taek, who is wearing the yellow belt.)

2428
01:25:11,347 --> 01:25:12,807
(He spots something.)

2429
01:25:13,277 --> 01:25:14,546
He's my first target.

2430
01:25:14,547 --> 01:25:15,777
(Accidentally exposing the red tail)

2431
01:25:15,817 --> 01:25:17,417
Okay. I should rip off Joon's tail first.

2432
01:25:18,087 --> 01:25:19,956
It's Joon. I saw it.

2433
01:25:19,957 --> 01:25:21,017
(Luckily, he spotted his prey before the start.)

2434
01:25:21,117 --> 01:25:23,357
There's no easy target right now.

2435
01:25:24,087 --> 01:25:25,586
Ki Taek seems relatively easy now.

2436
01:25:25,587 --> 01:25:27,026
(He wants to send Ki Taek to a deserted island.)

2437
01:25:27,027 --> 01:25:28,427
Because he hasn't fully adjusted yet,

2438
01:25:28,857 --> 01:25:30,127
he won't be so tough.

2439
01:25:30,367 --> 01:25:31,567
That's the moment to strike.

2440
01:25:32,297 --> 01:25:35,667
Since Ki Taek hasn't been here long,

2441
01:25:36,267 --> 01:25:39,837
it would be good to give him a nice experience.

2442
01:25:40,537 --> 01:25:42,577
Shouldn't Ki Taek go there at least once?

2443
01:25:43,447 --> 01:25:46,407
Everything is just too easy for him right now.

2444
01:25:46,877 --> 01:25:49,476
Even if I have to go, I want to go a bit later.

2445
01:25:49,477 --> 01:25:52,487
(He has no idea that he is being showered with the members' love.)

2446
01:25:52,687 --> 01:25:55,557
(Nervous)

2447
01:25:56,217 --> 01:25:59,897
(Will he be able to avoid being sent to the deserted island?)

2448
01:26:00,027 --> 01:26:01,126
Ready.

2449
01:26:01,127 --> 01:26:02,297
I'll go this way.

2450
01:26:02,857 --> 01:26:03,867
Start.

2451
01:26:04,927 --> 01:26:08,237
(Off to an energetic start)

2452
01:26:08,467 --> 01:26:11,307
(Cautious)

2453
01:26:11,607 --> 01:26:13,837
(The maximum level of alert)

2454
01:26:14,337 --> 01:26:18,747
(DinDin charges toward Joon, who has the red tail)

2455
01:26:19,977 --> 01:26:21,576
(Give me the red tail.)

2456
01:26:21,577 --> 01:26:23,746
- It's you. Let's form an alliance.
- It's an alliance.

2457
01:26:23,747 --> 01:26:25,716
But I have to rip off your tail first.

2458
01:26:25,717 --> 01:26:28,587
- I have to get your tail first.
- No.

2459
01:26:28,657 --> 01:26:30,556
- I'll just take one tail from you.
- No.

2460
01:26:30,557 --> 01:26:32,126
- Can't you trust me?
- No.

2461
01:26:32,127 --> 01:26:34,897
- I promise. Don't you trust me?
- No.

2462
01:26:35,027 --> 01:26:37,726
(Meanwhile, Ki Taek is approaching these two.)

2463
01:26:37,727 --> 01:26:38,966
- Why can't you trust me?
- For now...

2464
01:26:38,967 --> 01:26:40,996
- Anyway, I will...
- I'll get mine in no time.

2465
01:26:40,997 --> 01:26:43,137
What's your color? You should avoid the attack.

2466
01:26:43,337 --> 01:26:44,366
He's hiding it.

2467
01:26:44,367 --> 01:26:45,367
(They spot Ki Taek.)

2468
01:26:45,767 --> 01:26:47,177
I'm Ki Taek's target.

2469
01:26:47,237 --> 01:26:48,937
Ki Taek is wearing the yellow belt.

2470
01:26:49,077 --> 01:26:50,506
- Let's do this as Team YB.
- Okay.

2471
01:26:50,507 --> 01:26:51,906
- Do you know the easiest way?
- Hey.

2472
01:26:51,907 --> 01:26:53,276
Come here.

2473
01:26:53,277 --> 01:26:55,016
If you play tricks here,

2474
01:26:55,017 --> 01:26:57,446
- Come here.
- I'll break your wrists.

2475
01:26:57,447 --> 01:27:00,117
- Just come here.
- Seriously, I'll change right away.

2476
01:27:00,357 --> 01:27:02,557
For now, the 3 of us are 1.

2477
01:27:02,787 --> 01:27:04,526
If anyone plays tricks here,

2478
01:27:04,527 --> 01:27:06,126
we'll be strangers.

2479
01:27:06,127 --> 01:27:07,826
Team YB will last long.

2480
01:27:07,827 --> 01:27:09,626
We will have to keep doing things as Team YB. Okay?

2481
01:27:09,627 --> 01:27:11,396
The moment you do this, I'll slap your wrist away.

2482
01:27:11,397 --> 01:27:12,926
- You can't do things like this.
- Exactly.

2483
01:27:12,927 --> 01:27:15,667
- Promise me.
- I promise. I'm serious.

2484
01:27:15,797 --> 01:27:18,007
(Meanwhile, Jong Min is watching them from afar.)

2485
01:27:18,267 --> 01:27:20,206
Those brats are plotting something.

2486
01:27:20,207 --> 01:27:22,336
Just look at them cooking up a plan.

2487
01:27:22,337 --> 01:27:23,507
Those wicked brats.

2488
01:27:23,707 --> 01:27:26,206
Ki Taek has the green tail. His first tail is green.

2489
01:27:26,207 --> 01:27:27,747
I'm going to run in the direction Ki Taek is going.

2490
01:27:28,377 --> 01:27:30,886
- He's over there.
- We need to corner him like this.

2491
01:27:30,887 --> 01:27:32,887
Hey, I'll go this way. You two should go together.

2492
01:27:33,017 --> 01:27:34,516
I think I can take care of this by myself.

2493
01:27:34,517 --> 01:27:36,986
(Team YB scatters to start the hunt for Jong Min.)

2494
01:27:36,987 --> 01:27:37,987
Let's go.

2495
01:27:37,988 --> 01:27:40,197
(Cautious and vigilant)

2496
01:27:40,597 --> 01:27:43,027
- DinDin.
- Hey, don't try to pull a trick.

2497
01:27:43,097 --> 01:27:45,066
Hey, let's go and get Jong Min.

2498
01:27:45,067 --> 01:27:46,126
- Go to Jong Min and...
- Let's go.

2499
01:27:46,127 --> 01:27:48,096
Let's go and try to talk Jong Min into this.

2500
01:27:48,097 --> 01:27:49,097
(Betraying Joon as soon as he leaves)

2501
01:27:49,098 --> 01:27:50,567
I think we should go after Joon first.

2502
01:27:50,637 --> 01:27:52,466
(Hesitant)

2503
01:27:52,467 --> 01:27:54,137
(Staring at DinDin's yellow tail)

2504
01:27:54,207 --> 01:27:57,007
(Eyes fixed on his tail)

2505
01:27:57,447 --> 01:27:59,546
- You...
- DinDin, hang on.

2506
01:27:59,547 --> 01:28:01,546
We're not supposed to keep each other in check.

2507
01:28:01,547 --> 01:28:03,116
- We shouldn't be doing this.
- But you...

2508
01:28:03,117 --> 01:28:04,886
This is just my second time meeting you.

2509
01:28:04,887 --> 01:28:06,246
Why are you being so cautious?

2510
01:28:06,247 --> 01:28:07,487
No. Come here.

2511
01:28:07,687 --> 01:28:10,987
It's not actually good for me to face Jong Min.

2512
01:28:13,427 --> 01:28:15,827
(Jong Min takes off as soon as he sees DinDin.)

2513
01:28:16,297 --> 01:28:18,127
Jong Min!

2514
01:28:18,397 --> 01:28:20,496
(Sensing danger, he breaks into a full sprint.)

2515
01:28:20,497 --> 01:28:21,696
(Jong Min quickly hides himself in an alley.)

2516
01:28:21,697 --> 01:28:23,197
- Jong Min!
- What?

2517
01:28:24,637 --> 01:28:27,737
(Hearing something, Joon quickly comes to the alley.)

2518
01:28:27,807 --> 01:28:28,877
Jong Min!

2519
01:28:29,637 --> 01:28:30,647
What?

2520
01:28:30,877 --> 01:28:33,347
(He spots Lee Joon's blue belt and runs away.)

2521
01:28:33,617 --> 01:28:34,876
(Where are you going?)

2522
01:28:34,877 --> 01:28:36,546
Hang on a second.

2523
01:28:36,547 --> 01:28:37,847
(Surrounded by Team YB's coordinated attack)

2524
01:28:37,947 --> 01:28:39,816
- What? Red?
- Doesn't he have the blue tail?

2525
01:28:39,817 --> 01:28:41,116
It's at the bottom.

2526
01:28:41,117 --> 01:28:44,056
- Doesn't he have the blue tail?
- It's at the bottom.

2527
01:28:44,057 --> 01:28:46,387
(Jong Min is about to lose one of his tails.)

2528
01:28:46,457 --> 01:28:48,957
(Hearing the sound, Ki Taek approaches them.)

2529
01:28:49,057 --> 01:28:50,766
- Grab his arm.
- It's at the bottom.

2530
01:28:50,767 --> 01:28:52,227
- Grab him.
- The blue tail.

2531
01:28:52,397 --> 01:28:53,697
(He spots Ki Taek with the green tail.)

2532
01:28:53,997 --> 01:28:56,497
(Rushing toward Ki Taek like Wasp Man)

2533
01:28:56,597 --> 01:28:57,866
(Running away)

2534
01:28:57,867 --> 01:29:00,007
(Panting)

2535
01:29:00,207 --> 01:29:02,537
(Giving up after a short while due to lack of stamina)

2536
01:29:02,637 --> 01:29:05,647
(Meanwhile, Joon quickly pursues Jong Min.)

2537
01:29:05,907 --> 01:29:08,047
(Jong Min is in danger of losing one of his tails.)

2538
01:29:09,777 --> 01:29:11,686
(Lee Joon's camera)

2539
01:29:11,687 --> 01:29:14,417
(Jong Min's blue tail is eliminated.)

2540
01:29:15,857 --> 01:29:18,757
(With the blue tail gone, his tail turns red.)

2541
01:29:18,927 --> 01:29:21,827
(Jong Min is left with only 2 tails after losing 1.)

2542
01:29:21,957 --> 01:29:23,896
(I did it.)

2543
01:29:23,897 --> 01:29:25,126
I'll help you.

2544
01:29:25,127 --> 01:29:27,796
(DinDin suddenly tries to form an alliance with Jong Min?)

2545
01:29:27,797 --> 01:29:29,637
You pretend to run away.

2546
01:29:29,837 --> 01:29:31,066
You should catch Ki Taek.

2547
01:29:31,067 --> 01:29:32,606
- Where's Ki Taek?
- You catch Ki Taek first.

2548
01:29:32,607 --> 01:29:33,977
I bet Ki Taek is your target.

2549
01:29:34,337 --> 01:29:36,877
(Approaching him the moment his back is turned)

2550
01:29:37,407 --> 01:29:38,546
(Turning around)

2551
01:29:38,547 --> 01:29:39,876
(Do you think I'd fall for that again?)

2552
01:29:39,877 --> 01:29:40,947
You wicked...

2553
01:29:41,717 --> 01:29:43,517
(Disappointed)

2554
01:29:44,147 --> 01:29:45,187
Ki Taek.

2555
01:29:46,017 --> 01:29:47,987
You should catch Joon, and...

2556
01:29:48,187 --> 01:29:50,157
While you're holding Joon, Ki Taek... Get him!

2557
01:29:50,787 --> 01:29:52,526
- Why are you doing this?
- I'm helping you.

2558
01:29:52,527 --> 01:29:54,827
- Wait.
- You can catch Joon now.

2559
01:29:55,827 --> 01:29:57,426
(DinDin can attack them both with the red tails.)

2560
01:29:57,427 --> 01:29:59,666
(Torn)

2561
01:29:59,667 --> 01:30:01,296
You should grab Joon.

2562
01:30:01,297 --> 01:30:02,366
Okay. I will.

2563
01:30:02,367 --> 01:30:03,406
- You have to get Joon first...
- Okay.

2564
01:30:03,407 --> 01:30:04,636
so I can rip off his tail.

2565
01:30:04,637 --> 01:30:05,637
I'll grab him.

2566
01:30:05,937 --> 01:30:07,106
(Instead of DinDin, Jong Min charges to catch Joon.)

2567
01:30:07,107 --> 01:30:08,937
- Grab Joon!
- I got him.

2568
01:30:09,007 --> 01:30:11,506
- Hey!
- You're supposed to hold him.

2569
01:30:11,507 --> 01:30:12,676
(DinDin's camera)

2570
01:30:12,677 --> 01:30:15,017
(Betraying him the moment his back is visible)

2571
01:30:15,217 --> 01:30:17,617
Don't be ridiculous. You were charging toward me.

2572
01:30:17,987 --> 01:30:19,917
No. Grab Joon for me.

2573
01:30:20,087 --> 01:30:21,816
(This time, Joon is trying to catch Jong Min.)

2574
01:30:21,817 --> 01:30:23,427
(Sneaking)

2575
01:30:23,657 --> 01:30:26,157
(DinDin approaches to target Joon's tail this time.)

2576
01:30:26,557 --> 01:30:28,426
(A total chaos)

2577
01:30:28,427 --> 01:30:29,427
Hang on.

2578
01:30:29,428 --> 01:30:31,567
(Caught off guard, Jong Min is captured by Joon.)

2579
01:30:32,127 --> 01:30:34,937
(DinDin, who is after Jong Min, is right in front of him.)

2580
01:30:35,297 --> 01:30:38,407
(Spotting the chance to pluck Jong Min's red tail)

2581
01:30:38,437 --> 01:30:40,607
(Jong Min is in danger again due to Team YB's attack.)

2582
01:30:42,207 --> 01:30:43,406
(DinDin's camera)

2583
01:30:43,407 --> 01:30:45,677
(Jong Min's red tail is eliminated.)

2584
01:30:46,247 --> 01:30:48,847
(After losing one more tail, he's left with one yellow tail.)

2585
01:30:49,147 --> 01:30:51,516
(He fell for Team YB's alliance yet again.)

2586
01:30:51,517 --> 01:30:53,016
(Darn it.)

2587
01:30:53,017 --> 01:30:55,086
(He's off to the deserted island if he loses one more tail.)

2588
01:30:55,087 --> 01:30:56,887
- Did you get it?
- I did.

2589
01:30:57,287 --> 01:30:59,857
Joon, the situation looks a bit strange, so...

2590
01:31:01,527 --> 01:31:03,257
- Things don't look good.
- What?

2591
01:31:03,727 --> 01:31:05,426
Joon, the situation looks a bit strange, so...

2592
01:31:05,427 --> 01:31:07,736
(DinDin's camera)

2593
01:31:07,737 --> 01:31:09,997
(He gets rid of Joon's red tail, too.)

2594
01:31:10,267 --> 01:31:12,636
(Betraying him again right after achieving his goal)

2595
01:31:12,637 --> 01:31:13,777
Things don't look good!

2596
01:31:13,807 --> 01:31:15,606
(As expected of Bat DinDin)

2597
01:31:15,607 --> 01:31:16,677
What just happened?

2598
01:31:18,607 --> 01:31:19,607
What just happened?

2599
01:31:19,608 --> 01:31:20,617
(Nice words)

2600
01:31:21,577 --> 01:31:24,147
(Meanwhile, Jong Min is down to his last tail.)

2601
01:31:24,547 --> 01:31:27,387
(Once the yellow tail is removed, he's off to the deserted island.)

2602
01:31:27,587 --> 01:31:30,017
(It's over once he's caught by Ki Taek with the yellow belt.)

2603
01:31:33,757 --> 01:31:36,527
(Ki Taek closes in right behind Jong Min.)

2604
01:31:36,757 --> 01:31:39,397
(He tries to run away in a hurry.)

2605
01:31:39,467 --> 01:31:42,397
(Probably because he's exhausted, he's running slowly.)

2606
01:31:45,267 --> 01:31:46,806
(Ki Taek's camera)

2607
01:31:46,807 --> 01:31:51,077
(Jong Min's final tail is eliminated.)

2608
01:31:51,247 --> 01:31:52,507
You go on ahead.

2609
01:31:52,747 --> 01:31:53,747
Have the boat ready.

2610
01:31:53,748 --> 01:31:55,017
Jong Min, now Joon...

2611
01:31:55,217 --> 01:31:56,546
Don't even talk about Joon.

2612
01:31:56,547 --> 01:31:58,147
What? Is Jong Min out?

2613
01:31:58,487 --> 01:32:00,257
No. I just got Joon's tail.

2614
01:32:00,357 --> 01:32:02,616
All right. You all worked hard.

2615
01:32:02,617 --> 01:32:04,157
The mission is over.

2616
01:32:04,257 --> 01:32:07,127
Jong Min has lost all his tails.

2617
01:32:07,827 --> 01:32:09,196
- I lost them all.
- Yes.

2618
01:32:09,197 --> 01:32:12,227
You've been chosen for the third deserted island check-in.

2619
01:32:12,297 --> 01:32:13,737
Please get ready to leave.

2620
01:32:13,897 --> 01:32:14,897
I'll get going, you brats.

2621
01:32:16,967 --> 01:32:18,006
Good luck.

2622
01:32:18,007 --> 01:32:19,206
(Trudging along)

2623
01:32:19,207 --> 01:32:21,207
- We will see you there.
- Things will be all set there.

2624
01:32:22,077 --> 01:32:23,677
Now that Jong Min is gone,

2625
01:32:23,877 --> 01:32:26,647
you can enjoy your rest now.

2626
01:32:27,177 --> 01:32:29,177
(What?)

2627
01:32:29,317 --> 01:32:30,617
You rude punks!

2628
01:32:32,187 --> 01:32:33,447
You rude punks!

2629
01:32:33,717 --> 01:32:34,917
(Laughing)

2630
01:32:35,617 --> 01:32:37,427
Just wait until you get to my age.

2631
01:32:37,987 --> 01:32:39,357
He sounds like a foul-mouthed grandma.

2632
01:32:39,487 --> 01:32:40,997
"Just wait until you get to my age."

2633
01:32:41,527 --> 01:32:42,996
I used to be really fast.

2634
01:32:42,997 --> 01:32:44,867
(How cruel time is.)

2635
01:32:44,997 --> 01:32:46,866
Back when I was a dance singer, I was in my prime.

2636
01:32:46,867 --> 01:32:47,996
I'm still a dance singer, though.

2637
01:32:47,997 --> 01:32:51,006
(His youth flashes before his eyes.)

2638
01:32:51,007 --> 01:32:53,166
Why are my legs giving out? Did I lose all my muscle tension?

2639
01:32:53,167 --> 01:32:56,876
(Heading to the deserted island, longing for his young days.)

2640
01:32:56,877 --> 01:32:57,877
I'm thirsty.

2641
01:32:57,878 --> 01:32:59,747
(Next episode)

2642
01:33:00,447 --> 01:33:04,547
(What on earth drives them this crazy?)

2643
01:33:05,047 --> 01:33:07,557
(The never-ending deserted island check-in)

2644
01:33:07,987 --> 01:33:11,656
(For those who fail to win,)

2645
01:33:11,657 --> 01:33:13,057
(the night on the deserted island awaits.)

2646
01:33:13,487 --> 01:33:16,496
(If you want to avoid the deserted island,)

2647
01:33:16,497 --> 01:33:18,527
(throw your whole body into it.)

2648
01:33:18,827 --> 01:33:21,897
(A mud-splattering struggle that you've never seen before)

2649
01:33:22,067 --> 01:33:24,067
(This is legendary.)

2650
01:33:24,507 --> 01:33:26,937
(It's no holds barred when it comes to victory.)

2651
01:33:27,107 --> 01:33:30,577
(From mocking attacks to cause a mental breakdown...)

2652
01:33:30,877 --> 01:33:33,717
(to slapstick comedy that crushes others' morale)

2653
01:33:34,277 --> 01:33:37,487
(Who will be the one to escape the deserted island?)

2654
01:33:37,747 --> 01:33:39,487
(See you next week.)
